{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","code":"MAT","content":["- Berean Study Bible"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Matthew"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Matthew"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Matthew"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Matthew"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Matthew"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Genealogy of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../ruth/4.htm#18|>Ruth 4:18–22</a>; <a href =|../luke/3.htm#23|>Luke 3:23–38</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the record of the genealogy of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Abraham was the father of  Isaac, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Isaac the father of  Jacob, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Jacob the father of  Judah and  his brothers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Judah  was the father of  Perez and  Zerah by  Tamar, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Perez  the father of  Hezron, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Hezron the father of  Ram. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>Aram</i>, a variant of <i>Ram</i>; also in verse 4; see 1 Chronicles 2:9–10."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Ram  was the father of  Amminadab, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Amminadab  the father of  Nahshon, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Nahshon the father of  Salmon. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Salmon  was the father of  Boaz by  Rahab, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Boaz  the father of  Obed by  Ruth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Obed the father of  Jesse, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"and Jesse the father of  David the king. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Next: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["David was the father of  Solomon by  Uriah’s wife, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Solomon  the father of  Rehoboam, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Rehoboam  the father of  Abijah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Abijah the father of  Asa. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>Asaph</i>, a variant of <i>Asa</i>; also in verse 8; see 1 Chronicles 3:10."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Asa  was the father of  Jehoshaphat, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Jehoshaphat the father of  Joram, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Joram the father of  Uzziah. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Uzziah  was the father of  Jotham, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jotham  the father of  Ahaz, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Ahaz the father of  Hezekiah. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Hezekiah  was the father of  Manasseh, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Manasseh  the father of  Amon, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>Am&#333;s</i>, a variant spelling of Amon; twice in this verse; see 1 Chronicles 3:14."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Amon the father of  Josiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"and Josiah the father of  Jeconiah and  his brothers "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["at the time of the exile to Babylon. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"After  the exile to Babylon: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jeconiah was the father of  Shealtiel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Shealtiel the father of  Zerubbabel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Zerubbabel  the father of  Abiud, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Abiud  the father of  Eliakim, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Eliakim the father of  Azor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Azor  was the father of  Zadok, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Zadok  the father of  Achim, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Achim the father of  Eliud. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Eliud  was the father of  Eleazar, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Eleazar  the father of  Matthan, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Matthan the father of  Jacob, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"and Jacob the father of  Joseph, the husband of Mary, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of whom was born Jesus, who is called Christ. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"In all, then, there were fourteen   generations from Abraham to David,  fourteen  from David to the exile to Babylon, and fourteen  from the exile  to the Christ. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Birth of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/7.htm#10|>Isaiah 7:10–16</a>; <a href =|../luke/2.htm|>Luke 2:1–7</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"}," This is how the birth  of Jesus Christ came about : His mother Mary was pledged in marriage  to Joseph, but before they came together, she was found to be with child   through the Holy Spirit. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Because Joseph  her husband was a righteous man and  was unwilling  to disgrace her publicly, he resolved to divorce her quietly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But after he had pondered these things,  an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream and said, Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid  to embrace Mary as your wife, for the One conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"She will give birth to  a Son, and you are to give Him the name Jesus, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Jesus</i> means <i>The LORD saves</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"because He will save  His people from  their sins. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"All  this took place to fulfill what  the Lord had said through the prophet : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Behold, the virgin will be with child   "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and will give birth to a son, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and they will call  Him  Immanuel” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>they will call His name Immanuel</i>; Isaiah 7:14 (see also DSS)"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["( which means ,  God with us” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Isaiah 7:14, Isaiah 8:8, and Isaiah 8:10."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"When  Joseph woke up   , he did as the angel of the Lord had commanded him and embraced Mary as his wife. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"But he had no union  with her ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:25 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>he did not know her</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"until  she gave birth to a Son. And he gave Him the name    Jesus. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Pilgrimage of the Magi"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../micah/5.htm|>Micah 5:1–6</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"After  Jesus was born in Bethlehem  in Judea, during the time  of King Herod,  Magi from the east arrived in Jerusalem, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"asking, Where is the One who has been born King of the Jews?  We saw His  star in the east ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>as it rose</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and have come to worship Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"When  King Herod heard this, he was disturbed, and all Jerusalem with him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And when he had assembled all the chief priests and scribes of the people, he asked  them where the Christ was to be born. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"In Bethlehem  in Judea,   they replied , for this is what  the prophet has written: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"But you, Bethlehem, in the land of Judah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["are by no means least among the rulers of Judah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for out of you will come a ruler "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who will be the shepherd  of My people  Israel.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Micah 5:2; see also 2 Samuel 5:2."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then Herod called the Magi secretly and learned from them the exact time the star had appeared. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And sending them to Bethlehem, he said: Go and search carefully for the Child, and when you find Him, report to me, so that I too may go and worship Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," After they had heard the king, they went on their way, and  the star  they had seen in the east went ahead of them until  it stood over the place where the Child was. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"When they saw the star, they rejoiced   with great delight. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"On coming to the house, they saw the Child with  His mother Mary, and they fell down and worshiped Him. Then they opened  their treasures and presented Him with gifts of gold and frankincense and myrrh. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And having been warned in a dream not to return to Herod, they withdrew to  their country by another route. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Flight to Egypt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../hosea/11.htm|>Hosea 11:1–7</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"When the Magi had gone,  an angel of the Lord appeared  to Joseph in a dream. Get up! he said. Take the Child and  His mother and flee to Egypt.  Stay there until  I tell you, for Herod is going to search for the Child  to kill Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"}," So he got up, took the Child and  His mother by night, and withdrew to Egypt, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"}," where he stayed until the death of Herod. This fulfilled what  the Lord had spoken through the prophet : Out of Egypt I called  My Son.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hosea 11:1"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Weeping and Great Mourning"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../jeremiah/31.htm|>Jeremiah 31:1–25</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"When Herod saw that he had been outwitted by the Magi,  he was filled with rage.  Sending orders, he put to death all the boys  in Bethlehem and    its vicinity who were two years old and under, according to the time  he had learned from the Magi. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Then what was spoken through the prophet Jeremiah  was fulfilled: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"A voice is heard in Ramah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["weeping and great mourning, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Rachel weeping for  her children "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and refusing  to be comforted, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because they are no more.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Jeremiah 31:15"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Return to Nazareth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/2.htm#39|>Luke 2:39–40</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"After  Herod died,  an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Get up! he said. Take the Child and  His mother and go to the land of Israel, for those seeking the  Child’s life are now dead. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"}," So Joseph got up, took the Child and  His mother, and went to the land of Israel. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"But when he learned that Archelaus was reigning in  Judea in place of  his father Herod, he was afraid to go there. And having been warned in a dream, he withdrew to the district  of Galilee, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"and he went and lived in a town called Nazareth. So was fulfilled what was spoken through the prophets:  He will be called a Nazarene. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Mission of John the Baptist"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/40.htm|>Isaiah 40:1–5</a>; <a href =|../mark/1.htm|>Mark 1:1–8</a>; <a href =|../luke/3.htm|>Luke 3:1–20</a>; <a href =|../john/1.htm#19|>John 1:19–28</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"}," In  those days John the Baptist came, preaching in the wilderness  of Judea ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"and saying, Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is near. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," This is he who was spoken of through the prophet Isaiah : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["A voice of one calling in the wilderness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Prepare the way for the Lord, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["make straight paths  for Him.’” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Isaiah 40:3 (see also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"}," John   wore   a garment of camel’s hair, with a leather belt around  his waist.   His food was locusts and wild honey. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"}," People went out to him from Jerusalem and all  Judea and the whole region around the Jordan. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"}," Confessing  their sins, they were baptized by him in the Jordan River. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"But when John saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming to his place of  baptism, he said to them, You brood of vipers, who warned you to flee from the coming wrath? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Produce fruit, then, in keeping with  repentance. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And do not presume to say to yourselves, We have  Abraham as our father. For I tell you that out of  these stones  God can raise up children for Abraham. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"The axe   lies ready at the root of the trees, and every tree  that does not produce good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"I  baptize you with water ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>in water</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"for repentance,  but after me will come One more powerful than I, whose  sandals I am not worthy to carry. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>in the Holy Spirit and in fire</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"His  winnowing fork is in  His hand  to clear  His threshing floor and to gather  His wheat into the barn; but He will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Baptism of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/1.htm#9|>Mark 1:9–11</a>; <a href =|../luke/3.htm#21|>Luke 3:21–22</a>; <a href =|../john/1.htm#29|>John 1:29–34</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"At that time  Jesus came from  Galilee to the Jordan     to be baptized by John. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"}," But John tried to prevent Him, saying, I  need to be baptized by You, and do You come to me? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Let it be so now,   Jesus replied   .  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["It is fitting for us to fulfill all righteousness in this way. Then John permitted Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"As soon as  Jesus was baptized,  He went up out of the water.  Suddenly the heavens were opened, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NA, BYZ, and TR <i>the heavens were opened to Him</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and He saw ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>and he saw</i>; see John 1:32–33."]}],"caller":"+"},"the Spirit of God descending like a dove and resting on Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"And  a voice from  heaven said, This is  My  beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased! "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Temptation of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/1.htm#12|>Mark 1:12–13</a>; <a href =|../luke/4.htm|>Luke 4:1–13</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then  Jesus was led by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the devil. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," After fasting forty days and forty nights,  He was hungry. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," The tempter came to Him and said, If You are the Son  of God, tell  these  stones to become bread. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"}," But Jesus answered , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["It is written:  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Man  shall not live on bread alone, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but on every word that comes from the mouth of God.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Deuteronomy 8:3"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then the devil took Him to the holy city and set Him on the pinnacle of the temple. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"If You are the Son  of God,  he said , throw Yourself down. For it is written: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He will command   His angels concerning You, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and  they will lift You up in their hands, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["  so that You will not strike  Your foot "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["against a stone.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 91:11–12"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Jesus replied  ,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["It is also written: Do not put  the Lord  your God to the test.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Deuteronomy 6:16"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Again, the devil took Him to a very high mountain and showed Him all the kingdoms of the world and  their glory. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"All this I will give You,  he said , if You will fall down and worship me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Away from Me, Satan!  Jesus told him . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For it is written: Worship the Lord  your God and serve Him only.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Deuteronomy 6:13"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Then the devil left Him, and  angels came and ministered to Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Begins His Ministry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/9.htm|>Isaiah 9:1–7</a>; <a href =|../mark/1.htm#14|>Mark 1:14–15</a>; <a href =|../luke/4.htm#14|>Luke 4:14–15</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"When Jesus heard that John had been imprisoned, He withdrew to  Galilee. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"}," Leaving  Nazareth, He went and lived in Capernaum, which is by the sea in the region of Zebulun and Naphtali, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"to fulfill what was spoken through the prophet Isaiah : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Land of Zebulun "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and land of Naphtali, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the Way of the Sea, beyond the Jordan, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Galilee of the Gentiles —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"the people  living in darkness "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["have seen a great light; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" on those living in the land  of the shadow of death, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a light has dawned .” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Isaiah 9:1–2"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"From that time on Jesus began  to preach  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is near. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The First Disciples"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/1.htm#16|>Mark 1:16–20</a>; <a href =|../luke/5.htm|>Luke 5:1–11</a>; <a href =|../john/1.htm#35|>John 1:35–42</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"}," As Jesus was walking beside the Sea  of Galilee, He saw two brothers, Simon  called Peter and  his brother Andrew. They were casting a net into the sea, for they were fishermen. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Come, follow  Me,  Jesus said , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and I will make you fishers of men. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"}," And at once they left their nets and followed Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"}," Going on from there, He saw two other brothers, James son  of Zebedee and  his brother John. They were in  a boat with  their father Zebedee, mending  their nets.  Jesus called them, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," and immediately they left the boat and  their father and followed Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Heals the Multitudes"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/3.htm#7|>Mark 3:7–12</a>; <a href =|../luke/6.htm#17|>Luke 6:17–19</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," Jesus went throughout   Galilee, teaching in  their synagogues,  preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every disease and  sickness among the people. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"  News about Him spread all over  Syria, and people brought to Him all who were ill with various diseases,  those suffering acute pain,  the demon-possessed,  those having seizures, and the paralyzed, and He healed them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"}," Large crowds followed Him, having come from  Galilee,  the Decapolis, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:25 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Ten Cities"]}],"caller":"+"}," Jerusalem,  Judea, and beyond the Jordan. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Sermon on the Mount"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"When Jesus saw the crowds, He went up on the mountain and  sat down.  His disciples came to Him, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"and He began    to teach them, saying: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Beatitudes"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../psalms/1.htm|>Psalm 1:1–6</a>; <a href =|../luke/6.htm#20|>Luke 6:20–23</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Blessed are the poor in spirit, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for theirs is the kingdom of heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Blessed are those who mourn, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for they will be comforted. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Blessed are the meek, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for they will inherit the earth. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Blessed are those who exercise strength under control, for they will inherit the land</i>; see Psalm 37:11."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for they will be filled. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Blessed are the merciful, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for they will be shown mercy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Blessed are the pure  in heart, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for they will see  God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Blessed are the peacemakers, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for they will be called sons of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Blessed are those who are persecuted because of righteousness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for theirs is the kingdom of heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Blessed are you when people insult you,  persecute you, and falsely say all kinds of evil against you because of Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Rejoice and be glad, because great is  your reward in  heaven, for in the same way they persecuted the prophets  before you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Salt and Light"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/9.htm#49|>Mark 9:49–50</a>; <a href =|../luke/14.htm#34|>Luke 14:34–35</a>; <a href =|../philippians/2.htm#12|>Philippians 2:12–18</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"You are the salt of the earth. But if the salt loses its savor, how  can it be made salty again? It is no longer good  for anything, except  to be thrown out and trampled by  men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"You are the light of the world. A city  on a hill ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>A city lying on a hill</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"cannot  be hidden. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Neither do people light a lamp and put it under  a basket. Instead, they set it on  a stand, and it gives light to everyone  in the house. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"In the same way, let your light shine before  men, that they may see your  good deeds and glorify  your Father  in  heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Fulfillment of the Law"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Do not think that I have come to abolish the Law or the Prophets. I have not come  to abolish them, but to fulfill them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For I tell you truly, until   heaven and  earth pass away, not  a single jot, not a stroke of a pen, will disappear from the Law until  everything is accomplished. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"}," So then, whoever breaks one of the  least of these commandments and teaches  others to do likewise will be called least in the kingdom of heaven; but whoever  practices and teaches them  will be called great in the kingdom of heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"For I tell you that unless  your  righteousness exceeds  that of the scribes and Pharisees, you will never enter    the kingdom of heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Anger and Reconciliation"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/12.htm#57|>Luke 12:57–59</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"You have heard that it was said to the ancients, Do not murder  ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Exodus 20:13; Deuteronomy 5:17"]}],"caller":"+"},"and Anyone who  murders will be subject to judgment.’ ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"But I tell you that anyone who is angry with  his brother ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i>without cause</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"will be subject to judgment. Again, anyone who  says to his brother, Raca,’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Raca</i> is an Aramaic expression of contempt."]}],"caller":"+"},"will be subject to the Sanhedrin. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the Council</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"But anyone who  says, You fool! will be subject to the  fire of hell. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the hell of fire</i>; Greek <i>the Gehenna of fire</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"So if you are offering  your gift at the altar and there remember that  your brother has something against you, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"leave  your gift there before the altar.  First go and be reconciled to your brother;  then come and offer  your gift. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"}," Reconcile quickly   with your adversary, while  you are still on the way to court. Otherwise ,  he may hand you over  to the judge, and the judge may hand you over to the officer, and you may be thrown into prison. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Truly I tell you,   you will not get out  until  you have paid the last penny. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>kodrant&#275;n</i>; that is, a Roman copper coin worth about 1/64 of a denarius"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Adultery"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../leviticus/18.htm|>Leviticus 18:1–30</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"You have heard that it was said, Do not commit adultery .’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Exodus 20:14; Deuteronomy 5:18"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"But I tell you that anyone  who looks at a woman to  lust after her has already committed adultery with her in  his heart. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"}," If  your  right eye causes you to sin , gouge it out  and throw it away .  It is better for you to lose one   part of your body than for  your whole  body to be thrown into hell. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>Gehenna</i>; also in verse 30"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And if  your right hand causes you to sin , cut it off  and throw it away .  It is better for you to lose one   part of your body than for  your whole  body to depart into hell. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Divorce"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../deuteronomy/24.htm|>Deuteronomy 24:1–5</a>; <a href =|../luke/16.htm#18|>Luke 16:18</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"It has also been said , Whoever  divorces  his wife must give her a certificate of divorce.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Deuteronomy 24:1"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"But I tell you that anyone  who divorces  his wife, except for sexual immorality, brings adultery upon her. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:32 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>causes her to commit adultery</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"And he who  marries a divorced woman commits adultery. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Oaths and Vows"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../numbers/30.htm|>Numbers 30:1–16</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Again, you have heard that it was said to the ancients, Do not break your oath , but fulfill  your vows to the Lord. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:33 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Numbers 30:2"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"But I tell you not to swear at all: either by  heaven, for it is  God’s throne; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"or by the earth, for it is His footstool   ; or by Jerusalem, for it is the city of the great King. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Nor should you swear by  your head, for you cannot  make a single hair white or black. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Simply let  your  Yes be ‘Yes, and your ‘No, No. Anything  more  comes from the evil one. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:37 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>from evil</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Love Your Enemies"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../leviticus/24.htm#17|>Leviticus 24:17–23</a>; <a href =|../luke/6.htm#27|>Luke 6:27–36</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"You have heard that it was said, Eye for eye and tooth for tooth.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:38 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Exodus 21:24; Leviticus 24:20; Deuteronomy 19:21"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"But I tell you not to resist an evil person.  If someone slaps you on  your right cheek, turn to him the other also; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"}," if someone wants to sue you and take  your tunic, let him have  your cloak as well; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"and if someone forces you to go  one mile, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:41 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>one milion</i>; that is, a Roman mile, approximately 4,855 feet or 1,480 meters"]}],"caller":"+"},"go with him two miles. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:41 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>go with him two.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"Give to the one who asks you, and do not turn away from  the one who wants to borrow from you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"You have heard that it was said, Love  your neighbor’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:43 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Leviticus 19:18"]}],"caller":"+"},"and Hate  your enemy. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"But I tell you, love  your enemies and pray for those who persecute you, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:44 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>love your enemies, bless those who curse you, do good to those who hate you, and pray for those who spitefully accuse you and persecute you</i>; see Luke 6:27–28."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"that you may be sons of your Father  in heaven.  He causes  His sun to rise on the evil and the good, and sends rain on the righteous and the unrighteous. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"}," If you love those who love you, what reward will you get? Do not even  tax collectors do the same? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"And if you greet only  your brothers, what are you doing more than others? Do not even  Gentiles do the same? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"Be  perfect, therefore, as  your  heavenly Father is perfect. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Giving to the Needy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../deuteronomy/15.htm#7|>Deuteronomy 15:7–11</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Be careful   not to perform your righteous acts ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>charitable acts</i> or <i>alms</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"before  men   to be seen by them. If you do , you will have no reward from  your Father  in  heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"So when you give to the needy , do not sound a trumpet  before you, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and on the streets, to be honored by  men. Truly I tell you, they already have  their full reward. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"But when you give to the needy , do not let  your left hand know what  your right hand is doing, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"so that your  giving may be in  secret. And  your Father , who sees  what is done in secret, will reward you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Lord’s Prayer"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/11.htm|>Luke 11:1–4</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"And when you pray, do not be  like the hypocrites. For they love to pray standing in the synagogues and on the  street corners  to be seen  by men. Truly I tell you, they already have  their full reward. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"But  when you pray, go into  your inner room,  shut  your door, and pray to your Father, who is   unseen. And  your Father, who sees  what is done in secret, will reward you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And when you pray, do not babble on  like  pagans, for they think that by  their many words they will be heard. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"}," Do not be like them, for  your Father knows what you need before  you ask Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"So then, this is how you should pray: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Our Father  in  heaven, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["hallowed be  Your name. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," Your kingdom come, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Your will be done, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" on earth as it is in heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Give us this day  our  daily bread. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And forgive us  our debts, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["as we also have forgiven  our debtors. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"And lead us not into temptation, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but deliver us from the evil one. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>from evil</i>; BYZ and TR include <i>For Yours is the kingdom and the power and the glory, forever. Amen.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"For if you forgive  men  their trespasses,  your  heavenly Father will also forgive  you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"But if you do not forgive   men  their trespasses, neither will your Father forgive  yours . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Proper Fasting"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"}," When you fast, do not be somber like the hypocrites, for they disfigure  their faces  to show  men they are fasting. Truly I tell you, they already have  their full reward. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"But when you fast, anoint your  head and wash  your face, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"so that your fasting will not be obvious   to men, but only to your Father, who is   unseen. And  your Father, who sees  what is done in secret, will reward you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Treasures in Heaven"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/12.htm#32|>Luke 12:32–34</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Do not store up for yourselves treasures on  earth, where moth and rust ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>worm</i>; also in verse 20"]}],"caller":"+"},"destroy, and where thieves break in and steal. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But store up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where moth and rust  do not destroy, and  where thieves do not break in  and steal. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For where  your treasure is, there  your heart will be also. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Lamp of the Body"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/11.htm#33|>Luke 11:33–36</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"The eye is the lamp of the body.  If  your eyes are good, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>If your eye is sound</i>; see Proverbs 22:9"]}],"caller":"+"}," your whole body will be full of light. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"But if  your eyes are bad, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>if your eye is evil</i>; see Proverbs 23:6 and Proverbs 28:22"]}],"caller":"+"},"your whole  body will be full of darkness. If then the light  within you is darkness, how great is that darkness! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"No one can serve two masters:  Either he will hate the one and love the other, or he will be devoted to the one and despise the other. You cannot  serve both God and money. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Do Not Worry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/12.htm#22|>Luke 12:22–31</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Therefore  I tell you, do not worry about  your life, what you will eat or  drink; or  about your body, what you will wear. Is not  life more than food, and the body more than clothes? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Look at the birds of the air:  They do not sow  or reap or gather into barns, and yet  your  heavenly Father feeds them. Are you not much more valuable than they? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"}," Who of you by worrying can add a single hour to  his life? ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>a single cubit to his height</i>; a cubit was approximately 18 inches or 45 centimeters."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"And why do you worry about clothes? Consider how the lilies of the field grow: They do not labor or spin. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Yet I tell you that not even Solomon in all  his glory was adorned like one of these. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"}," If that is how  God clothes the grass of the field, which is here today and tomorrow is thrown into the furnace, will He not much more clothe you, O you of little faith? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Therefore do not worry, saying, What shall we eat? or What shall we drink? or What shall we wear? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"For the Gentiles strive after all these things, and  your  heavenly Father knows that you need  them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"But seek first the kingdom of God ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:33 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["SBL, WH, and NE <i>seek first His kingdom</i>; see also Luke 12:31."]}],"caller":"+"},"and  His righteousness, and all these things will be added unto you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Therefore do not worry about  tomorrow,  for tomorrow will worry about itself.  Today has enough trouble  of its own. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Judging Others"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/6.htm#37|>Luke 6:37–42</a>; <a href =|../romans/14.htm|>Romans 14:1–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Do not judge, or  you will be judged. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"For with the same judgment you pronounce, you will be judged, and with the measure you use, it will be measured to you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," Why do you look at the speck  in   your brother’s eye  but fail to notice the beam in  your own eye? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"}," How can you say to your brother, Let me take the speck out of  your eye,’ while there is still  a beam in your own eye? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"You hypocrite! First take the beam out of  your own eye, and then you will see clearly to remove the speck from   your brother’s eye. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Do not give  dogs what is holy; do not throw  your pearls before  swine. If you do , they may trample them under  their feet, and then turn and tear you to pieces . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Ask, Seek, Knock"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/11.htm#5|>Luke 11:5–13</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Ask, and it will be given to you; seek, and you will find; knock, and the door will be opened to you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"For everyone  who asks receives;  he who seeks finds; and to him who knocks, the door will be opened. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," Which   of you, if his   son asks for bread, will give  him a stone? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Or if he asks for a fish, will give  him a snake? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"So if you who are evil know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father  in  heaven give good things to those who ask Him! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"In everything  , then,  do to others as  you would have  them do   to you. For this is the essence of the Law and the Prophets. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Narrow Gate"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/13.htm#22|>Luke 13:22–30</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Enter through the narrow gate. For wide is the gate and broad is the way that leads to  destruction, and many   enter through it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"But small is the gate and narrow the way that leads to  life, and only a few   find it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>A Tree and Its Fruit"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/6.htm#43|>Luke 6:43–45</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Beware of  false prophets. They come to you in sheep’s clothing, but inwardly they are ravenous wolves. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"By  their fruit you will recognize them.  Are grapes gathered  from thornbushes, or figs from thistles? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Likewise, every good tree bears good fruit,  but a bad tree bears bad fruit. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"A good tree cannot  bear bad fruit, and a bad tree cannot bear good fruit. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Every tree  that does not bear good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"So then, by  their fruit you will recognize them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Not everyone who says to Me, Lord, Lord, will enter  the kingdom of heaven, but only he who does the will  of My Father  in  heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Many will say to Me on that  day, Lord, Lord, did we not prophesy  in Your name, and in Your name drive out demons and    perform many miracles? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," Then I will tell them plainly ,  I never knew  you; depart from Me, you workers  of lawlessness! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The House on the Rock"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/6.htm#46|>Luke 6:46–49</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Therefore everyone who hears these  words of Mine and acts on them is like a wise man who built his  house on the rock. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"}," The rain fell,  the torrents raged, and the winds blew and beat against that  house; yet it did not fall , because its foundation was on the rock. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"But everyone who hears these  words of Mine and  does not act on them is like a foolish man who built his  house on  sand. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"}," The rain fell,  the torrents raged, and the winds blew and beat against that  house, and it fell— and great was  its collapse! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Authority of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"  When  Jesus had finished  saying these things, the crowds were astonished at  His teaching, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"because He taught  as one who had authority, and not as  their scribes. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Leper’s Prayer"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../leviticus/14.htm|>Leviticus 14:1–32</a>; <a href =|../mark/1.htm#40|>Mark 1:40–45</a>; <a href =|../luke/5.htm#12|>Luke 5:12–16</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"When Jesus came down from the mountain, large crowds followed Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Suddenly  a leper ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A <i>leper</i> was one afflicted with a skin disease. See Leviticus 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"came and knelt before Him, saying, Lord, if You are willing, You can make me clean . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," Jesus reached out His hand and touched the man. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I am willing, He said. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Be clean! And immediately his  leprosy was cleansed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Then  Jesus instructed him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["See that you don’t tell anyone . But go, show yourself to the priest and offer the gift  prescribed by Moses, as a testimony to them. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Leviticus 14:1–32."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Faith of the Centurion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/7.htm|>Luke 7:1–10</a>; <a href =|../john/4.htm#43|>John 4:43–54</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"When Jesus had entered  Capernaum, a centurion came  and pleaded with Him, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"  Lord,  my servant ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>child</i>; also in verses 8 and 13"]}],"caller":"+"},"lies at  home, paralyzed and in terrible agony. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I will go and heal him,  Jesus replied . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"}," The centurion answered , Lord, I am not worthy to have You come under my  roof. But just say the word, and  my servant will be healed. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"For I myself am a man under authority, with soldiers under me.  I tell one to go, and he goes, and another to come, and he comes. I tell  my servant to do something, and he does it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"When  Jesus heard this, He marveled and said to those following Him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Truly I tell you, I have not found anyone   in  Israel with such great faith. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"}," I say to you that many will come from the east and the west  to share the banquet with Abraham,  Isaac, and Jacob in the kingdom of heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But the sons of the kingdom will be thrown into the  outer darkness, where there will be  weeping and  gnashing  of teeth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then  Jesus said to the centurion, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Go! As you have believed, so will it be done for you. And  his servant was healed at that very  hour. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Heals at Peter’s House"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/1.htm#29|>Mark 1:29–34</a>; <a href =|../luke/4.htm#38|>Luke 4:38–41</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"When  Jesus arrived at Peter’s  house, He saw  Peter’s mother-in-law sick in bed  with a fever. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"So He touched  her hand, and the fever left her, and she got up and began to serve Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"When evening came, many who were demon-possessed were brought to Jesus, and He drove out the spirits with a word and healed all the  sick. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"This was to fulfill what was spoken through the prophet Isaiah : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He took up   our infirmities "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and carried our diseases.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Isaiah 53:4"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Cost of Discipleship"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/9.htm#57|>Luke 9:57–62</a>; <a href =|../luke/14.htm#25|>Luke 14:25–33</a>; <a href =|../john/6.htm#59|>John 6:59–66</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"When  Jesus saw a large crowd around Him, He gave orders to cross to the other side of the sea. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Sea of Galilee; Greek <i>to the other side</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"And one of the scribes came to Him and said, Teacher, I will follow You wherever  You go. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"  Jesus replied  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Foxes have dens and  birds of the air have nests,  but the Son  of Man has no place to lay His head. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"}," Another  of His disciples requested , Lord, first let me go and bury  my father. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"But  Jesus told him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Follow Me, and let the dead bury  their own dead. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Calms the Storm"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../psalms/107.htm|>Psalm 107:1–43</a>; <a href =|../mark/4.htm#35|>Mark 4:35–41</a>; <a href =|../luke/8.htm#22|>Luke 8:22–25</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"When He got into  the boat, His  disciples followed Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Suddenly  a violent storm came up on the sea, so that the boat was engulfed by the waves. But Jesus was sleeping. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"}," The disciples went and woke Him, saying, Lord, save us! We are perishing! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"You of little faith,  Jesus replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["why are you so afraid? Then He got up and rebuked the winds and the sea, and it was perfectly calm. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"  The men were amazed and asked, What kind of man is this?  Even the winds and the sea obey Him! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Demons and the Pigs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/5.htm|>Mark 5:1–20</a>; <a href =|../luke/8.htm#26|>Luke 8:26–39</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"When Jesus arrived on the other side in the region of the Gadarenes, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:28 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ, TR, and PT <i>Gergesenes</i>; other manuscripts <i>Gerasenes</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"He was met by  two demon-possessed men coming from the tombs. They were so violent that no one could pass  that  way. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"What do You want  with us, Son  of God?   they shouted . Have You come here to torture us before the appointed time? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"}," In the distance   a large herd of pigs was feeding. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"So the demons begged Jesus , If You drive us out , send us  into the herd  of pigs. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Go!  He told them.  So they came out and went into the pigs, and  the whole herd rushed down the steep bank into the sea and died in the waters. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"}," Those tending the pigs ran off   into the town and reported all this, including the account of the demon-possessed men. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Then  the whole town went out to meet  Jesus. And when they saw Him, they begged Him  to leave   their region. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Heals a Paralytic"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/2.htm|>Mark 2:1–12</a>; <a href =|../luke/5.htm#17|>Luke 5:17–26</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"}," Jesus got into  a boat, crossed over, and came to His own town. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Just then  some men brought ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>And behold, they brought</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"to Him a paralytic lying on a mat. When  Jesus saw  their faith, He said to the paralytic, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Take courage, son; your  sins are forgiven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"On seeing this , some of the scribes said to themselves, This man is blaspheming! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"But  Jesus knew ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NA, BYZ, and TR <i>saw</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"what they were thinking and said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Why  do you harbor evil in  your hearts? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"}," Which is easier: to say, Your  sins are forgiven, or to say, Get up and walk? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"But so that you may know that the Son  of Man has authority on  earth to forgive sins... Then He said to the paralytic, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Get up, pick up your  mat, and go    home. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And the man got up and went    home. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"When the crowds saw this, they were filled with awe and glorified  God,  who had given such authority  to men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Calls Matthew"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/2.htm#13|>Mark 2:13–17</a>; <a href =|../luke/5.htm#27|>Luke 5:27–32</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"As  Jesus went on from there, He saw a man named Matthew sitting at the tax booth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Follow Me,  He told him, and Matthew got up and followed Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Later, as Jesus was dining at Matthew’s house,   many tax collectors and sinners came and ate with  Him and  His disciples. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"When the Pharisees saw this, they asked  His disciples, Why   does your Teacher eat with  tax collectors and sinners? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"}," On hearing this, Jesus said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["It is not the healthy who need a doctor, but the  sick. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But go and learn what this means: I desire mercy,  not sacrifice.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hosea 6:6"]}],"caller":"+"},"For I have not come  to call the righteous, but sinners. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>but sinners, to repentance</i>; see Luke 5:32."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Questions about Fasting"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/2.htm#18|>Mark 2:18–20</a>; <a href =|../luke/5.htm#33|>Luke 5:33–35</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then John’s  disciples came to Jesus and asked, Why is it that  we and the Pharisees fast so often, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH do not include <i>so often</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}," but Your disciples do not fast? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"  Jesus replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["How can  the guests of the bridegroom mourn  while  He is with them? But the time will come when the bridegroom will be taken from them;  then they will fast. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Patches and the Wineskins"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/2.htm#21|>Mark 2:21–22</a>; <a href =|../luke/5.htm#36|>Luke 5:36–39</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"}," No one sews a patch of unshrunk cloth on an old garment. For the patch  will pull away from the garment, and a worse tear will result. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Neither do men pour new wine into old wineskins. If they do  , the skins will burst,  the wine will spill, and the wineskins will be ruined. Instead, they pour new wine into new wineskins, and both are preserved. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Healing Touch of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/5.htm#21|>Mark 5:21–43</a>; <a href =|../luke/8.htm#40|>Luke 8:40–56</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"While Jesus was saying  these things , a synagogue leader came and knelt before Him. My  daughter  has just died, he said . But come and place Your  hand on her, and she will live. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"So  Jesus got up and went with him, along with His  disciples. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Suddenly  a woman who had suffered from bleeding for twelve years came up behind Him and touched the fringe of His cloak. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"}," She said to herself, If only I touch His  cloak, I will be healed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"  Jesus turned and saw her. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Take courage, daughter, He said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["your  faith has healed you. And the woman was healed from that very hour. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"When  Jesus entered  the house of the synagogue leader,  He saw the flute players and the noisy crowd. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Go away, He told them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" The girl is not dead , but asleep. And they laughed at Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"After  the crowd had been put outside, Jesus went in and took the girl by the hand, and  she got up. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"And the news about this spread throughout  that  region. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Heals the Blind and Mute"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/7.htm#31|>Mark 7:31–37</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"As  Jesus went on from there, two blind men followed Him, crying out  , Have mercy on us, Son of David! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"After Jesus had entered  the house, the blind men came to Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Do you believe that I am able to do this?   He asked . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Yes, Lord, they answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Then He touched their  eyes and said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["According to your  faith will it be done to you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And their  eyes were opened.   Jesus warned them sternly  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["See that no one finds out about this! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"But  they went out and spread the news about Him throughout   the land. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"As they were leaving,  a demon-possessed man who was mute was brought to Jesus. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"And when the demon had been driven out, the man began to speak.  The crowds were amazed and said, Nothing like this has ever been seen in  Israel! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"But the Pharisees said, It is by the prince of demons that He drives out  demons. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Lord of the Harvest"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/10.htm|>Luke 10:1–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"  Jesus went through all the towns and  villages, teaching in their  synagogues,  preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every disease and  sickness. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"When He saw the crowds, He was moved with compassion for them, because they were harassed and helpless, like sheep without  a shepherd. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Then He said to His disciples,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The harvest is plentiful, but the workers are few. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Ask the Lord of the harvest, therefore,  to send out workers into His  harvest. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Twelve Apostles"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/3.htm#13|>Mark 3:13–19</a>; <a href =|../luke/6.htm#12|>Luke 6:12–16</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"And calling His twelve  disciples to Him, Jesus gave them authority over unclean spirits, so that they could drive them out  and heal every disease and  sickness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," These are the names of the twelve apostles: first Simon,  called Peter, and his  brother Andrew;  James son of Zebedee, and his  brother John; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Philip and Bartholomew; Thomas and Matthew the tax collector; James son  of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Simon the Zealot, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>Simon the Cananean</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and Judas  Iscariot, who  betrayed Jesus. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>the one also having betrayed Him</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Ministry of the Twelve"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/6.htm#7|>Mark 6:7–13</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm|>Luke 9:1–6</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"These  twelve  Jesus sent out  with the following instructions: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Do not go onto the road of the Gentiles or enter   any town of the Samaritans. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Go  rather to the  lost sheep  of Israel. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"As you go, preach this message:  The kingdom of heaven is near. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Heal the sick, raise the dead, cleanse the lepers, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A <i>leper</i> was one afflicted with a skin disease. See Leviticus 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"drive out demons. Freely you have received; freely give. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Do not carry any gold or silver or copper in your  belts. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Take no bag for the road, or second tunic, or sandals, or staff; for the worker is worthy of his provisions. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"  Whatever  town or village you enter, find out who is worthy there  and stay at his house ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>stay there</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"until  you move on. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"As you enter  the home, greet its occupants. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>greet it</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"  If the home is worthy, let your  peace rest on it, but if it is not , let your  peace return to you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"And if anyone   will not welcome you or heed your  words, shake the dust off your feet when you leave  that  home or  town. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Truly I tell you, it will be more bearable  for Sodom and Gomorrah on the day of judgment than for that  town. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Sheep among Wolves"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../2_timothy/1.htm#3|>2 Timothy 1:3–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Behold, I am sending you out  like sheep among  wolves; therefore be as shrewd as  snakes and as innocent as  doves. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"But beware of  men, for they will hand you over  to their councils and flog you in their  synagogues. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"}," On My account  you will be brought  before governors and kings as witnesses to them and to the Gentiles. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"But when they hand you over , do not worry about how to respond or what to say.  In that  hour you will be given what to say. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"For it will not be  you  speaking, but the Spirit of your Father  speaking through you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"}," Brother will betray brother to death, and a father his child;  children will rise against their parents and have them put to death . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," You will be hated by everyone because of My  name, but the one who perseveres to the end  will be saved. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," When they persecute you in one  town, flee to the next.  Truly I tell you, you will not reach   all the towns of Israel before  the Son of Man comes. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"A disciple is not above his teacher, nor a servant above his  master. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"It is enough for a disciple to be like his  teacher, and a servant like his  master. If the head of the house has been called Beelzebul, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:25 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["WH <i>Beezeboul</i>; Vulgate <i>Beelzebub</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"how much more the members of his household! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Fear God Alone"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/12.htm#4|>Luke 12:4–7</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"So do not be afraid  of them. For there is nothing concealed that  will not be disclosed, and nothing hidden that will not be made known . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"What I tell you in the dark, speak in the daylight;  what is whispered in your ear, proclaim from the housetops. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"}," Do not be afraid  of those who kill the body but cannot  kill the soul.  Instead, fear the One who can destroy both soul and body in hell. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:28 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>Gehenna</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Are not two sparrows sold for a penny? ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>an assarion</i>; that is, a Roman copper coin worth about 1/16 of a denarius"]}],"caller":"+"},"Yet not one of them will fall to the ground apart from the will of your  Father. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And even the very hairs of your head are all numbered. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"So do not be afraid ; you are worth more than many sparrows. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Confessing Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/12.htm#8|>Luke 12:8–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Therefore everyone who confesses  Me before  men,  I will also confess  him before My  Father  in  heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"But whoever  denies Me before  men,  I will also deny him before My  Father  in  heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Not Peace but a Sword"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../micah/7.htm|>Micah 7:1–6</a>; <a href =|../luke/12.htm#49|>Luke 12:49–53</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Do not assume that I have come to bring peace to the earth; I have not come  to bring peace, but a sword. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"For I have come to turn "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a man against his  father, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" a daughter against her  mother, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" a daughter-in-law against her  mother-in-law. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"  A man’s enemies will be the members "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of his own household.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:36 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Micah 7:6"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Anyone who loves his father or mother more than Me is not worthy of Me;  anyone who loves his son or daughter more than Me is not worthy of Me; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"and anyone who does not take up  his  cross and follow  Me is not worthy of Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"Whoever finds his  life will lose it, and whoever loses his  life for My sake  will find it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Reward of Service"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../2_kings/4.htm#8|>2 Kings 4:8–17</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"He who receives you receives Me, and he who receives Me receives the One who sent Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Whoever receives a prophet because he is  a prophet will receive a prophet’s reward, and whoever receives a righteous man because he is  a righteous man will receive a righteous man’s reward. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"And if anyone  gives even a cup of cold water to one of these  little ones  because he is My disciple, truly I tell you, he will never lose   his  reward. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>John’s Inquiry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/7.htm#18|>Luke 7:18–23</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"After    Jesus had finished instructing His twelve  disciples, He went on from there  to teach and preach in their  cities. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, in the towns of Galilee"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Meanwhile  John heard in  prison about the works of Christ, and he sent  his  disciples ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>he sent two of his disciples</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"to ask Him, Are You the One who was to come, or should we look for someone else? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"  Jesus replied  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Go back and report to John what you hear and see: ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The blind receive sight,  the lame walk, the lepers ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A <i>leper</i> was one afflicted with a skin disease. See Leviticus 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"are cleansed,  the deaf hear,  the dead are raised, and the good news is preached to the poor. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"}," Blessed is the one who does not fall away   on account of Me. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>who is not offended by Me</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Testifies about John"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../malachi/3.htm|>Malachi 3:1–5</a>; <a href =|../luke/7.htm#24|>Luke 7:24–35</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"}," As John’s disciples were leaving,  Jesus began to speak to the crowds about John: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What did you go out into the wilderness to see? A reed swaying in the wind? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Otherwise, what did you go out to see? A man dressed in fine clothes? Look, those  who wear fine clothing are found in   kings’ palaces. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"What then did you go out to see? A prophet? Yes, I tell you, and more than a prophet. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"This is the one about whom it is written: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Behold, I will send My  messenger ahead of You  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who will prepare Your  way before You.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Malachi 3:1"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Truly I tell you, among those born of women there has risen no one greater than John the Baptist. Yet even the least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"}," From the days of John the Baptist until now, the kingdom of heaven has been subject to violence, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>has been forcefully advancing</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and the violent lay claim to it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"For all the Prophets and the Law prophesied until John. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"And if you are willing to accept it, he is the Elijah  who was to come. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Malachi 4:5."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"He who has ears, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>ears to hear</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"let him hear. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"}," To what can I compare this  generation? They are like children sitting in the marketplaces and calling out  to others: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"}," We played the flute for you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and  you did not dance; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["we sang a dirge, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and  you did not mourn. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For John came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, He has a demon! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The Son  of Man came eating and drinking, and they say, Look at this glutton and drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners! But  wisdom is vindicated by her  actions. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Woe to the Unrepentant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/10.htm#13|>Luke 10:13–16</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Then Jesus began to denounce the cities in which  most of His miracles had been performed, because  they did not repent. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Woe to you, Chorazin! Woe to you, Bethsaida! For if the miracles that were performed in you had been performed in Tyre and Sidon,  they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"But I tell you, it will be more bearable for Tyre and Sidon on the day of judgment than for you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"And you, Capernaum,  will you be lifted up to heaven? No, you will be brought down to Hades! For if the miracles that were performed in you had been performed in Sodom,  it would have remained to this day. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"But I tell you that it will be more bearable  for Sodom on the day of judgment than for you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Rest for the Weary"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/10.htm#21|>Luke 10:21–24</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"At that  time  Jesus  declared, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I praise You, Father, Lord  of heaven and  earth, because You have hidden these things from the wise and learned, and revealed them to little children. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Yes,  Father, for this was well-pleasing in Your sight . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"All things have been entrusted to Me by My  Father.  No one knows the Son except  the Father, and no one knows the Father except  the Son and those to whom  the Son chooses to reveal Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Come to Me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I  will give you rest. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Take My  yoke upon you and learn from Me, for I am gentle and humble in heart, and you will find rest for your souls. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"For My  yoke is easy and My  burden is light. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Lord of the Sabbath"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../1_samuel/21.htm|>1 Samuel 21:1–7</a>; <a href =|../mark/2.htm#23|>Mark 2:23–28</a>; <a href =|../luke/6.htm|>Luke 6:1–5</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"At that  time  Jesus went through the grainfields on the Sabbath.  His  disciples were hungry and began to pick the heads of grain and eat them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," When the Pharisees saw this, they said to Him, Look, Your  disciples are doing what  is unlawful  on the Sabbath. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"  Jesus replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Have you not read what David did when he and his companions   were hungry? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"}," He entered  the house  of God, and he and his companions ate the consecrated bread  , ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the Bread of the Presence</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"which was not lawful for them     to eat, but  only for the priests. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Or  haven’t you read in the Law that on the Sabbath the priests in the temple break the Sabbath and yet are innocent? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"But I tell you that One greater than the temple is here. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"If only you had known  the meaning of I desire mercy,  not sacrifice,’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hosea 6:6"]}],"caller":"+"},"  you would not have condemned the innocent. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"For the Son of Man is Lord of the Sabbath. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Heals on the Sabbath"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/3.htm|>Mark 3:1–6</a>; <a href =|../luke/6.htm#6|>Luke 6:6–11</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," Moving on from there, Jesus entered  their  synagogue, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"and a man with a withered hand was there. In order to accuse Jesus,  they asked Him ,  Is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"  He replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["If  one  of you  has a sheep and it falls into a pit on the Sabbath,  will he not take hold of it and lift it out? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"}," How much more valuable is a man than a sheep! Therefore it is lawful to do good on the Sabbath. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then Jesus said to the man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Stretch out your  hand. So he stretched it out, and it was restored to full use, just like the other. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"But the Pharisees went out and plotted    how they might kill Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>God’s Chosen Servant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/42.htm|>Isaiah 42:1–9</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Aware of this ,  Jesus withdrew from that place.  Large crowds followed Him, and He healed them all, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"}," warning them  not to make Him known. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"This was to fulfill what was spoken through the prophet Isaiah : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Here is My  Servant, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["whom I have chosen, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["My  beloved, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in whom My  soul delights. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will put My  Spirit on Him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and He will proclaim justice to the nations. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"}," He will not quarrel or cry out; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["no one will hear His  voice in the streets. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"A bruised reed  He will not break, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a smoldering wick  He will not extinguish, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["till  He leads  justice to victory. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"}," In His name the nations will put their hope.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Isaiah 42:1–4 (see also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>A House Divided"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/3.htm#20|>Mark 3:20–27</a>; <a href =|../luke/11.htm#14|>Luke 11:14–23</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Then a demon-possessed man who was blind and mute was brought to Jesus, and He healed the man so that  he could speak and see. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," The crowds  were astounded and asked, Could this be   the Son of David? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"But when  the Pharisees heard this, they said, Only  by  Beelzebul, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["WH <i>Beezeboul</i>; Vulgate <i>Beelzebub</i>; also in verse 27"]}],"caller":"+"},"the prince  of demons, does this man  drive out  demons. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"}," Knowing their  thoughts, Jesus said to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Every kingdom divided against itself will be laid waste, and every city or household divided against itself  will not stand. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"}," If  Satan drives out  Satan, he is divided against himself. How then can his  kingdom stand? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"And if I drive out  demons by Beelzebul, by whom do your  sons drive them out? So then , they will be your judges. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"But if I drive out  demons by the Spirit of God, then the kingdom  of God has come upon you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Or again, how can anyone enter   a strong man’s  house and steal his  possessions, unless  he first ties up the strong man?  Then he can plunder his  house. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"He who is not with Me is against Me, and he who does not gather with Me scatters. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Unpardonable Sin"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/3.htm#28|>Mark 3:28–30</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Therefore  I tell you, every sin and blasphemy will be forgiven  men, but the blasphemy against the Spirit will not be forgiven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"  Whoever speaks a word against the Son  of Man will be forgiven , but  whoever speaks against  the Holy Spirit  will not be forgiven , either in this  age or in the one to come. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Good and Bad Fruit"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/6.htm#43|>Luke 6:43–45</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"}," Make a tree good and its  fruit will be good, or make a tree bad and its  fruit will be bad, for a tree is known by its fruit. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"You brood of vipers, how can you who are evil say anything good? For out of the overflow of the heart the mouth speaks. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"The good man brings good things out of his good store of treasure, and the evil man brings evil things out of his evil store of treasure. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"But I tell you that men will give an account   on the day of judgment for every careless word  they have spoken. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"For by your  words you will be acquitted, and by your  words you will be condemned. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Sign of Jonah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../jonah/3.htm|>Jonah 3:1–10</a>; <a href =|../luke/11.htm#29|>Luke 11:29–32</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Then some of the scribes and Pharisees said to Him  , Teacher, we want to see a sign from You. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"  Jesus replied  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["A wicked and adulterous generation demands a sign, but none  will be given it except  the sign of the prophet Jonah. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"For as Jonah was three days and three nights in the belly of the great fish, so the Son  of Man will be three days and three nights in the heart of the earth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"The men of Nineveh will stand at the judgment with this  generation and condemn it; for they repented at the preaching of Jonah, and now One greater than Jonah is here. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"The Queen of the South will rise at the judgment with this  generation and condemn it; for she came from the ends of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon, and now One greater than Solomon is here. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>An Unclean Spirit Returns"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/11.htm#24|>Luke 11:24–26</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"}," When an unclean spirit comes out of a man, it passes through arid places seeking rest and  does not find it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"Then it says, I will return to  the house  I left.  On its return, it finds the house vacant,  swept clean, and put in order. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"Then it goes and brings with it   seven other spirits more wicked than itself, and they go in and dwell there. And the final plight of that man is worse than the first. So  will it be  with this  wicked generation. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus’ Mother and Brothers"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/3.htm#31|>Mark 3:31–35</a>; <a href =|../luke/8.htm#19|>Luke 8:19–21</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"While Jesus was still speaking  to the crowds,  His  mother and  brothers stood outside, wanting to speak to Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"}," Someone told Him, Look, Your  mother and   brothers are standing outside, wanting to speak to You. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:47 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["WH does not include verse 47."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"But   Jesus replied   , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who is My  mother, and who are My  brothers? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"}," Pointing    to His  disciples, He said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Here are My  mother and My  brothers. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"For whoever  does the will of My  Father  in heaven  is My brother and sister and mother. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Sower"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/4.htm|>Mark 4:1–9</a>; <a href =|../luke/8.htm#4|>Luke 8:4–8</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"}," That same day  Jesus went out of the house and sat by the sea. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Such large crowds gathered around Him that He got into  a boat and sat down, while all the people stood on the shore. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"And He told them many things in parables, saying,   "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["A farmer went out  to sow his seed. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And as he was  sowing,  some seed fell along the path, and the birds came and devoured it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"}," Some fell on  rocky ground, where  it did not have much soil.  It sprang up quickly because the soil  was  shallow. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"But when the sun rose, the seedlings were scorched, and they withered because  they had no root. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"}," Other seed fell among  thorns,   which grew up and choked the seedlings. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Still other seed fell on  good  soil and produced a crop —    a hundredfold,   sixtyfold, or  thirtyfold. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"He who has ears, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>ears to hear</i>; also in verse 43"]}],"caller":"+"},"let him hear. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Purpose of Jesus’ Parables"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/6.htm|>Isaiah 6:1–13</a>; <a href =|../mark/4.htm#10|>Mark 4:10–12</a>; <a href =|../luke/8.htm#9|>Luke 8:9–10</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then the disciples came to Jesus and asked , Why  do You speak to the people in parables? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"  He replied  ,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The knowledge of the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven has been given to you, but not to them . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"}," Whoever has  will be given more, and he will have an abundance.  Whoever does not have, even what he has will be taken away from him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"This is why I speak to them in parables: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Though seeing,  they do not see; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["though hearing,  they do not hear or understand. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Deuteronomy 29:4, Isaiah 42:20, Jeremiah 5:21, and Ezekiel 12:2."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"}," In them the prophecy of Isaiah is fulfilled  : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You will be ever hearing  but never  understanding;  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you will be ever seeing  but never  perceiving. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"For  this  people’s heart has grown callous;  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they hardly hear  with their ears, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and they have closed their  eyes. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Otherwise  they might see with their eyes, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" hear with their ears,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["understand with their hearts, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and turn, and I would heal them.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Isaiah 6:9–10 (see also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But blessed are your  eyes because they see, and  your ears because they hear. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"For truly I tell you,  many prophets and righteous men longed to see what you see but  did not see it, and to hear what you hear but  did not hear it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Sower Explained"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/4.htm#13|>Mark 4:13–20</a>; <a href =|../luke/8.htm#11|>Luke 8:11–15</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"}," Consider, then, the parable of the sower: ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"When anyone hears the message of the kingdom but does not understand it, the evil one comes and snatches away what was sown in  his heart. This is the seed sown ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>the one sown</i>; also in verses 20, 22, and 23"]}],"caller":"+"},"along the path. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"}," The seed sown on  rocky ground  is the one who hears the word and at once receives it with joy. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"But since he has   no root, he remains for only a season. When trouble or persecution comes because of the word,  he quickly falls away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," The seed sown among the thorns  is the one who hears the word, but the worries of this life and the deceitfulness  of wealth choke the word, and it becomes unfruitful. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"But the seed sown on  good soil  is the one who hears the word and understands it. He indeed bears fruit and produces a crop —    a hundredfold,   sixtyfold, or  thirtyfold. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Weeds"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../ezekiel/17.htm|>Ezekiel 17:1–10</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Jesus put before them another parable : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The kingdom of heaven is like a man who sowed good seed in his  field. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"But while   everyone was asleep, his  enemy came and sowed weeds among  the wheat, and slipped away. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"}," When the wheat sprouted and bore grain, then the weeds also appeared. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"}," The  owner’s servants came to him and said, Sir,  didn’t you sow good seed in your  field? Where then did the weeds come from? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"An enemy  did this,   he replied . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So  the servants asked him,  Do you want us to go and pull them up ? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"No ,   he said, if you pull the weeds now, you might uproot the wheat with them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Let both grow together until the harvest.  At that time    I will tell the harvesters: First collect the weeds and tie them in bundles to  be burned ; then gather  the wheat into my  barn.’ "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Mustard Seed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/4.htm#30|>Mark 4:30–34</a>; <a href =|../luke/13.htm#18|>Luke 13:18–19</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"He put before them another parable : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The kingdom of heaven is like a mustard seed that a man took and planted in his  field. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Although it is the smallest of all  seeds, yet  it grows into  the largest of garden plants and becomes a tree, so that the birds of the air come and nest in its  branches. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Leaven"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/13.htm#20|>Luke 13:20–21</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"He told them still another parable: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The kingdom of heaven is like leaven that a woman took and mixed into three measures of flour, until all of it was leavened. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>I Will Open My Mouth in Parables"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../psalms/78.htm|>Psalm 78:1–72</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"}," Jesus spoke all these things to the crowds in parables.  He did not tell them anything   without using a parable. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"So was fulfilled what was spoken through the prophet : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will open My  mouth in parables; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will utter things hidden since the foundation of the world.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:35 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 78:2 (see also LXX); SBL, NE, and WH do not include <i>of the world</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Weeds Explained"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../zephaniah/1.htm|>Zephaniah 1:1–6</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Then Jesus dismissed the crowds and went into the house.  His  disciples came to Him and said, Explain to us the parable of the weeds in the field. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"  He replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The One who sows the good seed is the Son  of Man. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"  The field is the world, and  the good seed represents  the sons of the kingdom.   The weeds are the sons of the evil one, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"and the enemy  who sows them is the devil.  The harvest is the end of the age, and  the harvesters are angels. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"}," As the weeds are collected and burned in the fire, so will it be at the end of the age. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"The Son  of Man will send out His  angels, and they will weed out of His  kingdom every  cause of sin and all who practice  lawlessness. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"And they will throw them into the  fiery furnace, where there will be  weeping and  gnashing of teeth. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"Then the righteous will shine like the sun in the kingdom of their Father. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:43 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Daniel 12:3."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He who has ears, let him hear. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parables of the Treasure and the Pearl"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"The kingdom of heaven is like treasure hidden in  a field. When a man found it, he hid it again, and in his  joy he went and sold all  he had and bought that  field. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"Again, the kingdom of heaven is like  a merchant in search of fine pearls. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"When he found one very precious pearl, he went away and sold all  he had and bought it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Net"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"Once again, the kingdom of heaven is like a net that was cast into the sea and caught  all kinds of fish. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"}," When it was full, the men pulled it   ashore. Then they sat down and sorted the good fish into containers, but threw the bad away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"So will it be at the end of the age: The angels will come and separate the wicked from  the righteous ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"and throw them into the  fiery furnace, where there will be  weeping and  gnashing of teeth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"Have you understood all these things? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Yes, they answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"Then  He told them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For this reason , every scribe who has been discipled in the kingdom of heaven is like  a homeowner who brings out of his  storeroom new treasures as well as old. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Rejection at Nazareth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/6.htm|>Mark 6:1–6</a>; <a href =|../luke/4.htm#16|>Luke 4:16–30</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"  When  Jesus had finished these  parables, He withdrew from that place. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"}," Coming to His hometown  , He taught the people in their  synagogue, and they were astonished. Where did this man get  such  wisdom and  miraculous powers?  they asked. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"Isn’t  this the  carpenter’s son? Isn’t His  mother’s name Mary, and aren’t His  brothers James,  Joseph, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:55 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>Joses</i>; see Mark 6:3."]}],"caller":"+"}," Simon, and Judas? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"Aren’t  all His  sisters with us as well? Where then did this man get all these things? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57"},"And they took offense at Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But  Jesus said to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Only  in his hometown and in  his own household is a prophet  without honor. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58"},"And  He did not do many miracles there, because of their  unbelief. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Beheading of John"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/6.htm#14|>Mark 6:14–29</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm#7|>Luke 9:7–9</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"At that  time Herod the tetrarch heard the reports about Jesus ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"and said to his servants, This is John the Baptist; he has risen from the dead!  That is why  miraculous powers are at work in him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Now  Herod had arrested  John and bound him and put him in prison on account of Herodias,  his  brother Philip’s wife, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"because John had been telling him ,  It is not lawful for you to have her. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Although Herod wanted to kill John, he was afraid of the people, because they regarded John as a prophet. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"On Herod’s birthday , however, the daughter  of Herodias danced before them   and pleased  Herod ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"so much that he promised with an oath to give to her whatever  she asked. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"}," Prompted by her  mother,  she said, Give me here on a platter the head of John the Baptist. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," The king was grieved, but because of his oaths and  his guests, he ordered that her wish be granted ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"and sent to have  John beheaded in the prison. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"}," John’s  head was brought in on a platter and presented to the girl,  who carried it to her mother. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then John’s  disciples came and took his body and buried it. And they went and informed  Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Feeding of the Five Thousand"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/6.htm#30|>Mark 6:30–44</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm#10|>Luke 9:10–17</a>; <a href =|../john/6.htm|>John 6:1–15</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"When  Jesus heard  about John , He withdrew  by boat  privately to a solitary place. But the crowds found out about it and followed Him on foot from the towns. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"When He stepped ashore and saw a large crowd,  He had compassion on them and healed their  sick. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"When evening came, the disciples came to Him and said, This is a desolate place, and the hour is already late .  Dismiss the crowds so they can go to the villages and buy themselves some food. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"They do not need to go away,   Jesus replied . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You give them something to eat. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"}," We have here only  five loaves of bread and two fish,   they answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Bring them here to Me,   Jesus said. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"And He directed the crowds to sit down on the grass. Taking the five loaves and the two fish and looking up to  heaven, He spoke a blessing. Then He broke the loaves and gave them to the disciples, and the disciples gave them to the people. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"  They all ate and were satisfied, and the disciples picked up twelve basketfuls   of broken pieces that were left over. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"About five thousand men  were  fed, besides women and children. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Walks on Water"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/6.htm#45|>Mark 6:45–52</a>; <a href =|../john/6.htm#16|>John 6:16–21</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," Immediately Jesus made the disciples get into  the boat and go on ahead of Him to the other side, while  He dismissed the crowds. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"After He had dismissed them  , He went up on the mountain by Himself to pray. When evening came, He was there alone, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"but the boat was already far  ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>many stadia</i>; a stadion was about 607 feet or 185 meters"]}],"caller":"+"},"from  land, buffeted by the waves because the wind was against it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"}," During the fourth watch of the night, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:25 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, between three and six in the morning"]}],"caller":"+"},"Jesus went out to them, walking on the sea. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"When the disciples saw Him walking on the sea, they were terrified. It’s a ghost! they said , and cried out in  fear. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"But Jesus spoke up  at once  : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Take courage! It is I. Do not be afraid. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Lord, if it is You,  Peter replied   , command me to come to You on the water. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Come  , said Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then Peter got down out of the boat,  walked on the water, and came toward  Jesus. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"But when he saw the strength of the wind, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>when he saw the strong wind</i>; NE and WH do not include <i>strong</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"he was afraid and, beginning to sink, cried out , Lord, save me! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"}," Immediately  Jesus reached out His hand and took hold of Peter. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You of little faith,  He said , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["why  did you doubt? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"And when they had climbed back into the boat, the wind died down. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Then those who were in the boat worshiped Him, saying, Truly You are the Son of God! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Heals at Gennesaret"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/6.htm#53|>Mark 6:53–56</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"When they had crossed over, they landed    at Gennesaret. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"And when the men of that  place recognized Jesus, they sent word to all  the surrounding region.  People brought all the  sick to Him ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"and begged Him just to let them touch the fringe of His cloak. And all who touched Him were healed. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Tradition of the Elders"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/7.htm|>Mark 7:1–13</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then some Pharisees and scribes came  to Jesus from Jerusalem and asked, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Why do  Your  disciples break the tradition of the elders?   They do not wash their  hands before they eat . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"  Jesus replied  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And why  do you break the command  of God for the sake of your  tradition? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"For  God said, Honor your father and  mother’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Exodus 20:12; Deuteronomy 5:16"]}],"caller":"+"},"and Anyone who curses his father or mother  must be put to death.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Exodus 21:17; Leviticus 20:9"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But you say that if anyone  says to his father or  mother, Whatever  you would have received from me is a gift devoted to God,’ ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"  he need not honor his  father or   mother with it. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and TR (see also Mark 7:12); literally <i>he need not honor his father or mother</i>; SBL, NA, WH, and BYZ do not include <i>or mother</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"Thus you nullify the word  of God for the sake of your  tradition. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"You hypocrites! Isaiah prophesied correctly about you : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"These  people honor Me with their lips, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but their  hearts are far  from Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," They worship Me in vain; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they teach as doctrine the precepts of men.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Isaiah 29:13 (see also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>What Defiles a Man"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/7.htm#14|>Mark 7:14–23</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," Jesus called the crowd to Him and said , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Listen and understand. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"A man is not defiled  by what enters  his mouth, but     by what comes out of  it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then the disciples came to Him and said, Are You aware that the Pharisees were offended when they heard this ? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But  Jesus replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Every plant that My  heavenly  Father  has not planted will be pulled up by its roots. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Disregard them! They are blind guides . ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>blind guides of the blind</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}," If a blind man leads a blind man, both will fall into a pit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"  Peter said  to Him, Explain this  parable to us. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Do you  still not understand?   Jesus asked. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"}," Do you not yet realize that whatever  enters  the mouth goes into the stomach and then is eliminated  ? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But the things that come out of the mouth come from the heart, and these things defile a man. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"For out of the heart come evil thoughts, murder, adultery, sexual immorality, theft, false testimony, and slander. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"These are what defile a man, but  eating with unwashed hands  does not defile  him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Faith of the Canaanite Woman"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/7.htm#24|>Mark 7:24–30</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"}," Leaving that place,  Jesus withdrew to the district of Tyre and Sidon. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"And  a Canaanite woman from  that region came to Him, crying out , Lord, Son of David, have mercy on me! My  daughter is miserably possessed by a demon. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"But   Jesus did not answer a word . So His  disciples came and urged Him , Send her away , for she keeps crying out after us. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"  He answered , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" I was sent only  to the  lost sheep of the house of Israel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"  The woman came and knelt before Him. Lord, help me! she said. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"But  Jesus replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["It is not right to take the  children’s bread and toss it to the dogs. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Yes, Lord,   she said,  even the dogs ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>puppies</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"eat  the crumbs  that fall from their  master’s  table. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"O woman,   Jesus answered  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["your  faith is great! Let it be done for you as you desire. And her  daughter was healed from that very hour. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Feeding of the Four Thousand"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../2_kings/4.htm#42|>2 Kings 4:42–44</a>; <a href =|../mark/8.htm|>Mark 8:1–10</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"}," Moving on from there,  Jesus went along the Sea  of Galilee. Then He went up on  a mountain and sat down. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"}," Large crowds came to Him, bringing   the lame, the blind, the crippled, the mute, and many others, and laid them at His  feet, and He healed them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"}," The crowd was amazed when they saw the mute speaking, the crippled restored,  the lame walking, and the blind seeing. And they glorified the God of Israel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Then  Jesus called His  disciples to Him and said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I have compassion for this crowd, because they have already been  with Me three days and have nothing  to eat.   I do not want to send them away  hungry,  or they may faint along the way. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"}," The disciples replied , Where in this desolate place could we find enough bread  to feed such a large crowd? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"How many loaves do you have?   Jesus asked . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Seven,   they replied, and a few small fish. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"And He instructed the crowd to sit down on the ground. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Taking the seven loaves and the fish,  He gave thanks and broke them. Then He gave them to the disciples, and the disciples gave them to the people. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"}," They all ate and were satisfied, and the disciples picked up seven basketfuls   of broken pieces that were left over. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"A total of  four thousand men were fed, besides women and children. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"After Jesus had dismissed the crowds, He got into  the boat and went to the region of Magadan. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Demand for a Sign"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/8.htm#11|>Mark 8:11–13</a>; <a href =|../luke/12.htm#54|>Luke 12:54–56</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then the Pharisees and Sadducees came and tested Jesus by asking Him to show them a sign from  heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"But  He replied  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When evening comes, you say, The weather will be fair, for the sky is red, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"and in the morning, Today it will be stormy, for the sky is red and overcast.  You know how to interpret the appearance of the sky, but not  the signs of the times. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Several manuscripts do not include <i>When evening comes... of the times.</i> from verses 2 and 3."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"A wicked and adulterous generation demands a sign, but  none will be given it except  the sign of Jonah. Then He left them and went away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/8.htm#14|>Mark 8:14–21</a>; <a href =|../luke/12.htm|>Luke 12:1–3</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"When they crossed to the other side, the disciples forgot to take bread. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Watch out!   Jesus told them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"  They discussed this among themselves and concluded, It is because  we did not bring any bread. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"}," Aware of their conversation , Jesus said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You of little faith, why are you debating among yourselves about having no bread? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," Do you still not understand?  Do you not remember the five loaves for the five thousand, and how many basketfuls you gathered? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Or the seven loaves for the four thousand, and how many basketfuls you gathered? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"How  do you not understand that  I was not telling you  about bread? But beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then they understood that  He was not telling them to beware of the leaven used in bread, but of the teaching of the Pharisees and Sadducees. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Peter’s Confession of Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/8.htm#27|>Mark 8:27–30</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm#18|>Luke 9:18–20</a>; <a href =|../john/6.htm#67|>John 6:67–71</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"When  Jesus came to the region of Caesarea  Philippi, He questioned His  disciples : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who  do people say the Son of Man is? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"  They replied, Some say John the Baptist;  others say Elijah; and still others, Jeremiah or one of the prophets. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"But what about you? Jesus asked . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who do you say I am? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"}," Simon Peter answered , You are the Christ, the Son of the living God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"  Jesus replied  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Blessed are you, Simon son of Jonah! ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>Simon Bar-Jonah</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"For this  was not revealed to you by flesh and blood, but by My  Father  in  heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"And I tell you that you are Peter, and on this  rock I will build My  church, and the gates of Hades  will not prevail against it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"I will give you the keys of the kingdom of heaven.  Whatever  you bind on  earth will be bound in  heaven, and whatever  you loose on  earth will be loosed in  heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Then He admonished the disciples  not to tell anyone  that He was the Christ. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Christ’s Passion Foretold"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/8.htm#31|>Mark 8:31–33</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm#21|>Luke 9:21–22</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"From that time on  Jesus ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH <i>Jesus Christ</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"began to show His  disciples that He must  go to Jerusalem and suffer many things at the hands of the elders,  chief priests, and scribes, and that He must be killed and on the third day be raised to life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"  Peter took Him aside  and began to rebuke Him. Far be it from You, Lord! he said. This shall never  happen to You! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"But  Jesus turned and said  to Peter, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Get behind Me, Satan! You are a stumbling block to Me. For  you do not have in mind the things  of God, but the things of men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Take Up Your Cross"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/8.htm#34|>Mark 8:34–38</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm#23|>Luke 9:23–27</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Then  Jesus told  His disciples, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["If anyone wants to come after Me, he must deny himself and take up his  cross and follow Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"For whoever  wants to save his  life will lose it, but whoever  loses his  life for My sake  will find it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"}," What will it profit a man if he gains the whole world, yet forfeits his  soul? Or what can a man give in exchange for his  soul? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"For the Son of Man will come in His  Father’s  glory with His  angels, and then He will repay each one according to what he  has done. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Truly I tell you,  some who are standing here    will not taste death before  they see the Son  of Man coming in His  kingdom. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Transfiguration"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/9.htm|>Mark 9:1–13</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm#28|>Luke 9:28–36</a>; <a href =|../2_peter/1.htm#16|>2 Peter 1:16–21</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"}," After six days  Jesus took with Him  Peter,  James,  and John the brother of James, and led them up   a high mountain by themselves. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"There He was transfigured before them.  His  face shone like the sun, and His  clothes became as white as the light. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Suddenly  Moses and Elijah appeared before them, talking with Jesus. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"  Peter  said  to Jesus, Lord, it is good for us to be here. If You wish, I will put up three shelters  ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>three tabernacles</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"one for You,  one for Moses, and one for Elijah. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"While Peter was still speaking , a bright cloud enveloped them, and  a voice from the cloud said, This is My  beloved  Son, in whom I am well pleased. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in 2 Peter 1:17"]}],"caller":"+"},"Listen to Him! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"When the disciples heard this, they fell facedown     in terror. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then  Jesus came over and touched them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Get up, He said. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["  Do not be afraid. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And when they looked up   , they saw no one except   Jesus . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"As they were coming down  the mountain,  Jesus commanded them , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Do not tell anyone  about this vision until  the Son  of Man has been raised from the dead. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," The disciples asked Him , Why then do the scribes say that Elijah must come first? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"   Jesus replied, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Elijah does indeed come, and he will restore all things. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But I tell you that Elijah has already come, and  they did not recognize him, but have done to him whatever they wished. In the same way , the Son  of Man will suffer at their hands . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then the disciples understood that He was speaking to them about John the Baptist. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Boy with a Demon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/9.htm#14|>Mark 9:14–29</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm#37|>Luke 9:37–42</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"When they came to the crowd, a man came up to Jesus and knelt before Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"}," Lord, have mercy on my  son, he said.  He has seizures and is suffering terribly.   He often falls into the fire or  into the water. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"}," I brought him to Your disciples, but they could not heal him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"O unbelieving and perverse generation!   Jesus replied . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["How long  must I remain with you? How long  must I put up with you? Bring the boy here to Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Then  Jesus rebuked the demon, and  it came out of the boy, and  he was healed from that  moment. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Power of Faith"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/17.htm#5|>Luke 17:5–10</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Afterward the disciples came  to Jesus  privately and asked, Why   couldn’t we drive it out ? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Because you  have so little faith,   He answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For truly I tell you, if you have faith the size of a mustard seed, you can say to this  mountain, Move from here to there, and it will move.  Nothing will be impossible for you.”</span> ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i><span class=|fnv|>21</span>But this kind does not come out except by prayer and fasting</i>; see Mark 9:29."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Second Prediction of the Passion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/9.htm#30|>Mark 9:30–32</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm#43|>Luke 9:43–45</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"When they gathered together in  Galilee,  Jesus told them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The Son  of Man is about to be delivered into the hands of men. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," They will kill Him, and on the third day He will be raised to life. And  the disciples were deeply grieved. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Temple Tax"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"After they had arrived in Capernaum, the collectors of the two-drachma tax ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>the didrachma</i>; twice in this verse"]}],"caller":"+"},"came  to Peter and asked, Does your  Teacher  pay the two drachmas? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Yes, he answered. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When Peter entered  the house,  Jesus preempted him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What  do you think, Simon? He asked. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["From whom do the kings of the earth collect customs and taxes: from their own sons, or from  others? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"From  others,  Peter answered. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then the sons are exempt,  Jesus said to him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"But so that  we may not offend them, go to the sea, cast a hook, and take the first fish you catch. When you open its  mouth, you will find a four-drachma coin. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>a stater</i>; that is, a silver coin worth approximately one shekel"]}],"caller":"+"},"Take it and give it to them for My tax and yours. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Greatest in the Kingdom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/9.htm#33|>Mark 9:33–41</a>; <a href =|../luke/9.htm#46|>Luke 9:46–50</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"At that  time the disciples came  to Jesus and asked, Who then is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," Jesus invited a little child to stand    among them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Truly I tell you,  He said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["unless  you change and become like  little children,   you will never enter  the kingdom of heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Therefore, whoever humbles himself like this  little child  is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"And whoever  welcomes a little child like this in My  name welcomes Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Temptations and Trespasses"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/9.htm#42|>Mark 9:42–48</a>; <a href =|../luke/17.htm|>Luke 17:1–4</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"But if anyone causes one of these  little ones who believe in Me to stumble, it would be better for him to have a large millstone hung around his  neck and to be drowned in the depths of the sea. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Woe to the world for the causes of sin.  These stumbling blocks must come, but woe to the man through whom  they come! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"}," If your  hand or your  foot causes you to sin , cut it off  and throw it away  . It is better for you to enter   life crippled or lame than to have two hands and two feet and be thrown into the  eternal fire. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And if your  eye causes you to sin , gouge it out  and throw it away  . It is better for you to enter   life with one eye than to have two eyes and be thrown into the fire of hell. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the hell of fire</i>; Greek <i>the Gehenna of fire</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Lost Sheep"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/15.htm|>Luke 15:1–7</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"See that  you do not look down on any of these  little ones. For I tell you that their  angels in heaven always  see the face of My Father  in heaven. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i><span class=|fnv|>11</span>For the Son of Man came to save the lost</i>; see Luke 19:10."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"What do you think? If a man has a hundred sheep and one of them goes astray,  will he not leave the ninety-nine  on the hills and go out to search for the one that is lost? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"And if he finds it, truly I tell you,  he rejoices more over that one sheep than over the ninety-nine    that did not go astray. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"In the same way,  your  Father  in heaven is not willing that any of these  little ones should perish. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>A Brother Who Sins"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../deuteronomy/19.htm#15|>Deuteronomy 19:15–21</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"}," If your  brother sins against you, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH do not include <i>against you</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"go and confront him privately    . If he listens to you, you have won your  brother over. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But if  he will not listen, take one or two others along , so that every matter may be established by the testimony of two or three witnesses.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Deuteronomy 19:15"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"}," If he refuses to listen to them, tell it to the church. And if he refuses to listen even to the church, regard him as you would a pagan or  a tax collector. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Truly I tell you, whatever  you bind on  earth will be bound in heaven, and whatever  you loose on  earth will be loosed in heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Ask in My Name"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../john/16.htm#23|>John 16:23–33</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Again, I tell you truly that if two of you on the earth agree about anything    you ask for, it will be done for you by My  Father  in heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"For where two or three  gather together in My  name, there am I with them  . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Unforgiving Servant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../romans/12.htm#14|>Romans 12:14–21</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Then Peter came to Jesus  and asked, Lord, how many times  shall I forgive  my  brother who sins against me? Up to seven times? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," Jesus answered , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I tell you, not just seven times, but  seventy-seven times !</span> ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>seventy times seven</i>; see Genesis 4:24 LXX"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Because of this, the kingdom of heaven is like  a king who wanted to settle accounts with his  servants. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"As he began the settlements, a debtor owing ten thousand talents ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent was worth about twenty years’ wages for a laborer."]}],"caller":"+"},"was brought to him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Since the man  was unable to pay, the master ordered that he be sold  to pay his debt, along with his wife and  children and everything  he owned. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Then the servant fell on his knees before him. Have patience with me, he begged, and I will pay back everything. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"}," His master    had compassion on him,  forgave his  debt, and released him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"But when  that servant went out, he found one of his  fellow servants who owed him a hundred denarii. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:28 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A denarius was customarily a day’s wage for a laborer; see Matthew 20:2."]}],"caller":"+"}," He grabbed him and began to choke him, saying, Pay back what you owe me!’ "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"So his  fellow servant fell down and begged him , Have patience with me, and I will pay you back. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"But   he refused. Instead, he went and had the man thrown  into prison until  he could pay his debt. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"When his  fellow servants saw what had happened,  they were greatly distressed, and they went and recounted all  of this to their master. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Then  the master summoned him and said , You wicked servant! I forgave  all your  debt because you begged me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Shouldn’t  you  have had mercy on your  fellow servant, just as I had on you? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"}," In anger his  master turned him over  to the jailers to be tortured, until  he should repay all that he owed . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"That is how  My  heavenly  Father will treat each of you unless  you forgive your  brother from your  heart. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Teachings about Divorce"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/10.htm|>Mark 10:1–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"  When  Jesus had finished saying these things  , He left   Galilee and went into the region  of Judea beyond the Jordan. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," Large crowds followed Him, and He healed them there. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Then some Pharisees came  and tested Him  by asking , Is it lawful for a man to divorce his  wife for any reason? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"  Jesus answered , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Have you not read that from the beginning the Creator made them male and female, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Genesis 1:27; Genesis 5:2"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"and said, For this reason  a man will leave his father and  mother and be united to his  wife, and the two will become  one flesh’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Genesis 2:24 (see also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"So they are no longer two, but one flesh. Therefore what  God has joined together, let man not separate. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Why then, they asked , did Moses order a man to give his wife a certificate of divorce and send her away ? ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Deuteronomy 24:1."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Jesus replied  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Moses permitted you to divorce your  wives because of your  hardness of heart. But it was not this way from the beginning. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Now I tell you that whoever  divorces his  wife, except for sexual immorality, and marries another woman commits adultery. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["SBL and BYZ include <i>And he who marries a divorced woman commits adultery</i>; see Matthew 5:32."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"His  disciples said to Him, If this is the case between a man and his wife, it is better not to marry. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Not everyone can accept this  word,   He replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but only those to whom it has been given. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"For there are eunuchs who    were born that way;   others  were made that way by  men; and  still others   live like eunuchs for the sake of the kingdom of heaven. The one who can accept this should accept it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Blesses the Children"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/10.htm#13|>Mark 10:13–16</a>; <a href =|../luke/18.htm#15|>Luke 18:15–17</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then little children were brought to Jesus for Him to place  His hands on them and pray for them. And the disciples rebuked those who brought them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"But  Jesus said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Let the little children come to Me, and  do not hinder them! For the kingdom of heaven belongs to such as these. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"And after He had placed His hands on them, He went on from there. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Rich Young Man"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/10.htm#17|>Mark 10:17–31</a>; <a href =|../luke/18.htm#18|>Luke 18:18–30</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Just then  a man came up to Jesus and inquired, Teacher, what good thing must I do to obtain eternal life? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Why do you ask Me about what is good? ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i><span class=|fnv|>16</span>...“Good Teacher, what good thing must I do to obtain eternal life?” <span class=|fnv|>17</span>“Why do you call Me good?”</i> See Mark 10:17–18 and Luke 18:18–19."]}],"caller":"+"},"  Jesus replied . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["There is only One who is good.  If you want to enter   life, keep the commandments. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Which ones? the man asked . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["  Jesus answered,   "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Do not murder,  do not commit adultery,  do not steal,  do not bear false witness, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"honor your father and  mother, and love your  neighbor as yourself.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Exodus 20:12–16; Leviticus 19:18; Deuteronomy 5:16–20"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"}," All these I have kept, said the young man . What  do I still lack? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"}," Jesus told him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["If you want to be perfect, go, sell your  possessions and give to the poor, and you will have treasure in heaven. Then come, follow Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"When the young man heard this  , he went away in sorrow, because he had great wealth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Then  Jesus said to His disciples, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Truly I tell you,  it is hard for a rich man to enter  the kingdom of heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"}," Again I tell you, it is easier for a camel to pass through the eye of a needle than for a rich man to enter  the kingdom of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"When the disciples heard this, they were greatly astonished and asked, Who then can be saved? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"  Jesus looked at them and said , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["With man this is impossible, but with God all things are possible. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Look,   Peter replied  , we have left everything  to follow You. What then will there be for us? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"  Jesus said to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Truly I tell you,  in the renewal of all things, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:28 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>in the regeneration</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"when the Son  of Man sits on His glorious throne, you who have followed Me   will also sit on twelve thrones, judging the twelve tribes  of Israel. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"And everyone who has left houses or brothers or sisters or father or mother or wife ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE, WH, and NA do not include <i>or wife</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"or children or fields for the sake of  My name will receive a hundredfold and will inherit eternal life. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"But many who are first will be last, and the last will be first. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Workers"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"For the kingdom of heaven is like  a landowner who went out early in the morning to hire workers for his  vineyard. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," He agreed to pay  them a denarius ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A denarius was customarily a day’s wage for a laborer; similarly in verses 9, 10, and 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"for the day and sent them into his  vineyard. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," About the third hour ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, about nine in the morning"]}],"caller":"+"},"he went out and saw others standing in the marketplace doing nothing. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"You also go into my vineyard,  he said , and I will pay you whatever  is right. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"So  they went. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" He went out again about the sixth hour and the ninth hour ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, about noon and again about three in the afternoon"]}],"caller":"+"},"and did the same thing. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"}," About the eleventh hour ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, about five in the afternoon; also in verse 9"]}],"caller":"+"},"he went out and found still others standing around. Why have you been standing here all  day long doing nothing?  he asked . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Because no one has hired us, they answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So he told them, You also go into my vineyard.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i>and whatever is right, you shall receive.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"When evening came, the owner of the vineyard said to his foreman, Call the workers and pay them their wages, starting with the last ones hired and moving on to the first. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," The workers who were hired about the eleventh hour came and each received a denarius. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"So when the original workers came, they assumed  they would receive more. But each of them also received  a denarius. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"}," On receiving their pay, they began to grumble against the landowner. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"These men who were hired last worked only one hour, they said, and you have made them equal to us who have borne the burden and the scorching heat of the day. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But  he answered one of them , Friend,  I am not being unfair to you.  Did you not agree with me on one denarius? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Take your pay and go.  I want to give this  last man the same as I gave you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"  Do I not have the right  to do as I please with what is mine? Or are you    envious because I am generous? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"So the last will be first, and the first will be last.”</span> ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i>For many are called, but few are chosen.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Third Prediction of the Passion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/10.htm#32|>Mark 10:32–34</a>; <a href =|../luke/18.htm#31|>Luke 18:31–34</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"As  Jesus was going up    to Jerusalem, He took the twelve disciples aside  and said , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Look, we are going up to Jerusalem, and the Son  of Man will be delivered over to the chief priests and scribes.  They will condemn Him to death ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"and will deliver Him over to the Gentiles  to be mocked and flogged and crucified. And on the third day He will be raised to life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>A Mother’s Request"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/10.htm#35|>Mark 10:35–45</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Then the mother of Zebedee’s  sons came to Jesus with her  sons and knelt down  to make a request  of Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"What do you want?   He inquired . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["She answered , Declare that in Your  kingdom one of these two  sons of mine may sit at Your right hand, and the other at Your left. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," You do not know what you are asking,   Jesus replied . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Can you drink the cup  I am going to drink?”</span> ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ includes <i>or be baptized with the baptism with which I am baptized.</i> TR is similar."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["We can, the brothers answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," You will indeed drink My  cup,”</span> ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i>and be baptized with the baptism with which I am baptized</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"Jesus said . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But  to sit at My right or  left  is not Mine to grant. These seats belong to those for whom  My  Father has prepared them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"When the ten heard about this, they were indignant with the two brothers. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"But  Jesus called them aside  and said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You know that the rulers of the Gentiles lord it over them, and their superiors exercise authority over them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"}," It shall not be this way among you. Instead, whoever  wants to become great among you must be your servant, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"and whoever  wants to be first among you must be your slave —  ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"just as the Son  of Man  did not come to be served, but to serve, and to give His  life as a ransom for many. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Blind Men by the Road"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/10.htm#46|>Mark 10:46–52</a>; <a href =|../luke/18.htm#35|>Luke 18:35–43</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"}," As they were leaving  Jericho, a large crowd followed Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And there were two blind men sitting beside the road. When they heard that Jesus was passing by, they cried out , Lord, Son of David, have mercy on us! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"}," The crowd admonished them  to be silent, but  they cried out all the louder , Lord, Son of David, have mercy on us! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"  Jesus stopped and called them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What do you want Me to do for you?  He asked. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Lord, they answered , let our  eyes be opened. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"}," Moved with compassion,  Jesus touched their  eyes, and at once they received their sight and followed Him. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Triumphal Entry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../zechariah/9.htm#9|>Zechariah 9:9–13</a>; <a href =|../mark/11.htm|>Mark 11:1–11</a>; <a href =|../luke/19.htm#28|>Luke 19:28–40</a>; <a href =|../john/12.htm#12|>John 12:12–19</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"}," As they approached  Jerusalem and came to Bethphage on the Mount  of Olives,  Jesus sent out two disciples, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"saying to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Go into the village  ahead of you, and at once you will find a donkey tied there, with her colt beside her. Untie them and bring them to Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," If anyone questions  you, tell him that the Lord  needs them, and he will send them right away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"}," This took place to fulfill what was spoken through the prophet : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Say to the Daughter of Zion, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["See, your  King comes to you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["gentle and riding on a donkey, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" on a colt, the foal of a donkey.’” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Zechariah 9:9"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"So the disciples went and did as  Jesus had directed them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"They brought the donkey and the colt and laid their cloaks on them, and Jesus sat on them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"  A massive crowd spread their  cloaks on the road, while others cut branches from the trees and spread them on the road. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," The crowds that went ahead of Him and those that followed were shouting : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Hosanna to the Son of David!” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Hosanna</i> is a transliteration of the Hebrew <i>Hosia-na</i>, meaning <i>Save, we pray</i> or <i>Save now</i>, which became a shout of praise; see Psalm 118:25; also in verse 15."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Blessed is He who comes in the name of the Lord!” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 118:26"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Hosanna in the highest!” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>“Hosanna in the highest heaven!”</i> See Psalm 118:25 and Psalm 148:1."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," When Jesus had entered  Jerusalem, the whole city was stirred and asked, Who is this? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"}," The crowds replied, This is Jesus, the prophet  from Nazareth  in Galilee. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Cleanses the Temple"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/11.htm#15|>Mark 11:15–19</a>; <a href =|../luke/19.htm#45|>Luke 19:45–48</a>; <a href =|../john/2.htm#12|>John 2:12–25</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then Jesus entered  the temple courts ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>the temple</i>; also in verses 15 and 23; BYZ and TR <i>the temple of God</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and drove out all who were buying and selling there  .  He overturned the tables of the money changers and the seats of those selling  doves. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"And He declared to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["It is written: My  house will be called a house of prayer.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Isaiah 56:7"]}],"caller":"+"},"But you are making it a den of robbers.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Jeremiah 7:11"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"}," The blind and the lame came to Him at the temple, and He healed them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"But the chief priests and  scribes were indignant when they saw the wonders  He performed and the children    shouting in the temple courts, Hosanna to the Son of David! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Do You hear what these children are saying?  they asked . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Yes,   Jesus answered .  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Have you never read: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" From the mouths of children and infants "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You have ordained praise’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 8:2 (see also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Then He left them and went out of the city to Bethany,  where He spent the night . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Barren Fig Tree"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/11.htm#12|>Mark 11:12–14</a>; <a href =|../mark/11.htm#20|>Mark 11:20–25</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"}," In the morning, as Jesus was returning to the city, He was hungry. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"}," Seeing a fig tree by the road, He went up to it but found nothing on it except   leaves. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" May you never bear      fruit again!  He said . And immediately the tree withered. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"When the disciples saw this, they marveled and asked, How did the fig tree wither so quickly? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Truly I tell you,   Jesus replied  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["if you have faith and do not doubt, not only will you do what was done to the fig tree, but even if you say to this  mountain, Be lifted up and thrown into the sea, it will happen. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," If you believe, you will receive whatever   you ask for in  prayer. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus’ Authority Challenged"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/11.htm#27|>Mark 11:27–33</a>; <a href =|../luke/20.htm|>Luke 20:1–8</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"When Jesus returned to the temple courts and began to teach, the chief priests and  elders of the people came up to Him. By what authority are You doing these things? they asked. And who gave You this  authority? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"}," I will also ask you one question,   Jesus replied  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" and if you answer Me, I will tell you by what authority I am doing these things. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"What was the source  of John’s  baptism? Was it from heaven or from men? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["  They deliberated among themselves and said, If we say, From heaven, He will ask , Why  then  did you not believe him? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"But if we say, From men, we are afraid of the people, for they all regard  John as a prophet. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"So they answered   ,  We do not know. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And Jesus replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Neither will I tell you by what authority I am doing these things. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Two Sons"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"But what do you think? There was a man who had two sons.  He went to the first one and said, Son, go and work today in the vineyard. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"I will not,   he replied .  But later he changed his mind and went. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH <i>But he went.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Then the man went to the second son and told him the same thing. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will, sir,   he said . But  he did not go. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Which of the two did the will of his father? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The first, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH <i>The latter</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"they answered. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Jesus said to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Truly I tell you,  the tax collectors and  prostitutes are entering  the kingdom  of God before you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"For John came to you in the way of righteousness, and  you did not believe him, but the tax collectors and  prostitutes did . And even after you saw this, you did not repent  and believe him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Wicked Tenants"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/12.htm|>Mark 12:1–12</a>; <a href =|../luke/20.htm#9|>Luke 20:9–18</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Listen to another parable: There was a landowner  who planted a vineyard.  He put a wall around it,  dug a winepress in it, and built a tower. Then he rented it out  to some tenants and went away on a journey. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"}," When the harvest time   drew near, he sent his  servants to the tenants to collect his  share of the fruit. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"But the tenants seized his  servants. They beat  one,  killed another, and stoned a third. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Again, he sent other servants, more than the first group. But the tenants did the same to them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"}," Finally, he sent his  son to them. They will respect my  son, he said. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"But when the tenants saw the son, they said to one another, This is the heir. Come, let us kill him and take his  inheritance. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"So they seized him and threw him out of the vineyard and killed him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"Therefore, when the owner of the vineyard returns, what will he do to those  tenants? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"He will bring those wretches to a wretched end, they replied , and will rent out the vineyard to other tenants who will give him his share of the fruit at  harvest time . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"}," Jesus said to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Have you never read in the Scriptures: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The stone  the builders rejected "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" has become the  cornerstone. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["This is from the Lord, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and it is marvelous in our eyes’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:42 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 118:22–23"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"Therefore  I tell you that the kingdom  of God will be taken away from you and given to a people who will produce its  fruit. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"}," He who falls on this  stone will be broken to pieces, but he on whom  it falls will be crushed . ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:44 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Tischendorf and some early manuscripts do not include verse 44; see also Luke 20:18."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"When the chief priests and  Pharisees heard His  parables, they knew that Jesus was speaking about them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Although they wanted to arrest Him, they were afraid of the crowds, because the people regarded Him as a prophet. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Banquet"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/14.htm#15|>Luke 14:15–24</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Once again,  Jesus spoke  to them in parables : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The kingdom of heaven is like  a king who prepared a wedding banquet for his son. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," He sent his  servants to call those he had invited to the banquet, but they refused  to come. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Again, he sent other servants and said, Tell those who have been invited that I have prepared my  dinner. My  oxen and  fattened cattle have been killed, and everything is ready. Come to the wedding banquet. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But  they paid no attention and went away,  one to his  field,  another to his  business. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"}," The rest seized his  servants, mistreated them, and killed them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"}," The king was enraged, and he sent his  troops to destroy those  murderers and burn their  city. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Then he said to his servants,  The wedding banquet is ready, but those I invited were not worthy. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Go therefore to the crossroads   and invite to the banquet as many as  you can find. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"So  the servants went out into the streets and gathered everyone  they could find, both evil and good, and the wedding hall was filled with guests. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"But when the king came in to see the guests, he spotted a man  who was not dressed in wedding clothes. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Friend,  he asked , how did you get in here  without wedding clothes? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But  the man was speechless. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then the king told the servants, Tie him hand and foot, and throw him  into the  outer darkness, where there will be  weeping and  gnashing of teeth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"For many are called, but few are chosen. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Paying Taxes to Caesar"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/12.htm#13|>Mark 12:13–17</a>; <a href =|../luke/20.htm#19|>Luke 20:19–26</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Then the Pharisees went out and conspired   to trap Jesus in His words. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"}," They sent their  disciples to Him along with the Herodians. Teacher, they said, we know that You are honest and that You teach the way  of God in accordance with the truth.  You seek favor from  no one, because  You pay no attention to external appearance . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"So tell us what You think: Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar or not? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But  Jesus knew their  evil intent and said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You hypocrites, why are you testing Me? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Show Me the coin used for the tax. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And  they brought Him a denarius. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A denarius was customarily a day’s wage for a laborer; see Matthew 20:2."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Whose  image is this,  He asked , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and whose inscription? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Caesar’s, they answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So  Jesus told them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Give to Caesar what is Caesar’s, and  to God what is  God’s. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"And when they heard this, they were amazed. So they left Him and went away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Sadducees and the Resurrection"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/12.htm#18|>Mark 12:18–27</a>; <a href =|../luke/20.htm#27|>Luke 20:27–40</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," That same day the Sadducees, who say there is no resurrection, came to Jesus and questioned Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Teacher, they said, Moses declared that if a man dies without having children, his  brother is to marry  the widow and raise up offspring for  him. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Deuteronomy 25:5"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Now there were seven brothers among us.  The first one married and died without having children. So he left his  wife to his brother. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"The same thing happened to  the second and  third brothers, down to the seventh. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"And last of all, the woman died. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"In the resurrection, then, whose wife will she be of the seven? For all of them were married to her. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"  Jesus answered  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You are mistaken because  you do not know the Scriptures or the power  of God. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"}," In the resurrection,  people will neither marry nor be given in marriage. Instead, they will be like the angels ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["SBL, BYZ, and TR <i>the angels of God</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"in  heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"But concerning the resurrection of the dead,  have you not read what   God said to you : ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"I am the God of Abraham,  the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:32 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Exodus 3:6"]}],"caller":"+"},"He is not the God of the dead, but of the living. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"When the crowds heard this, they were astonished at His  teaching. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Greatest Commandment"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../deuteronomy/6.htm|>Deuteronomy 6:1–19</a>; <a href =|../mark/12.htm#28|>Mark 12:28–34</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"And when the Pharisees heard that Jesus had silenced the Sadducees, they themselves gathered   together. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"}," One of them, an expert in the law, tested Him with a question: ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Teacher, which commandment is the greatest in the Law? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"  Jesus declared , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Love the Lord your  God with all your  heart and with all your  soul and with all your  mind.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:37 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Deuteronomy 6:5"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"This is the first and greatest commandment. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"And the second is like it: Love your  neighbor as yourself.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:39 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Leviticus 19:18"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"All the Law and the Prophets hang on these two  commandments. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Whose Son Is the Christ?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/12.htm#35|>Mark 12:35–37</a>; <a href =|../luke/20.htm#41|>Luke 20:41–44</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"While the Pharisees were assembled,  Jesus questioned them: ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"}," "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What do you think about the Christ? Whose son is He? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" David’s, they answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"Jesus said to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["How then does David in the Spirit call Him Lord’ For he says: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"The Lord said to my Lord, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Sit at My right hand "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["until  I put Your  enemies "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["under Your  feet.”’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:44 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 110:1"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"So if David calls Him Lord, how can He be David’s son? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"}," No one was able to answer  a word, and from that  day on no one dared to question Him any further. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"23"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Woes to Scribes and Pharisees"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/11.htm#37|>Luke 11:37–54</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then  Jesus spoke to the crowds and to His disciples: ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The scribes and  Pharisees sit in Moses’  seat. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"So practice and observe everything   they tell you. But do not do what they  do, for  they do not practice what they preach. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"}," They tie up heavy,  burdensome loads ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["SBL, NE, and WH <i>They tie up heavy loads</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and lay them on  men’s  shoulders, but they themselves  are not willing   to lift a finger to move them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"}," All their  deeds are done for  men  to see.  They broaden their  phylacteries and lengthen their tassels. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"}," They love the places of honor at  banquets,  the chief seats in the synagogues, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"}," the greetings in the marketplaces, and the title of ‘Rabbi’ by  which they are addressed. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>and to be called ‘Rabbi’ by men</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But you  are not to be called Rabbi, for you have one  Teacher, and you are all brothers. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And do not call anyone  on  earth your father, for you have one  Father, who is in heaven. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Nor are you to be called instructors, for you have one Instructor, the Christ. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"}," The greatest among you shall be your servant. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"For whoever exalts himself will be humbled, and whoever humbles himself will be exalted. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"}," Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, you hypocrites!  You shut the kingdom of heaven in men’s faces  .  You yourselves  do not enter, nor will you let in those who wish to enter. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i><span class=|fnv|>14</span>Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, you hypocrites! You defraud widows of their houses, and for a show make lengthy prayers. Therefore you will receive greater condemnation.</i> See Mark 12:40 and Luke 20:47."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, you hypocrites!  You traverse   land and sea to win a single convert, and when he becomes one, you make him twice as much a son of hell ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek <i>Gehenna</i>; also in verse 33"]}],"caller":"+"},"as you are. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Woe to you, blind guides! You say, If anyone  swears by the temple, it means nothing; but if anyone  swears by the gold of the temple, he is bound by his oath. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"You blind  fools!  Which is greater: the gold, or the temple  that makes it sacred  ? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"And you say, If anyone  swears by the altar, it means nothing; but if anyone  swears by the gift  on it, he is bound by his oath. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"You blind men!  Which is greater: the gift, or the altar  that makes it sacred  ? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"So then, he who swears by the altar swears by it and by everything  on it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"And he who swears by the temple swears by it and by the One who dwells in it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"And he who swears by  heaven swears by  God’s  throne and by the One who sits on it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, you hypocrites!  You pay tithes of  mint,   dill, and  cumin. But you have disregarded the weightier matters of the law:  justice,   mercy, and  faithfulness. You should have practiced the latter, without  neglecting the former. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"You blind guides!  You strain out  a gnat but swallow  a camel. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Leviticus 11:4 and Leviticus 11:23, where camels and gnats are both forbidden as food."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, you hypocrites!  You clean the outside of the cup and  dish, but inside they are full of greed and self-indulgence. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Blind Pharisee! First clean the inside of the cup and  dish, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NA does not include <i>and dish</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"so that  the outside may become clean as well. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, you hypocrites!  You are like whitewashed tombs, which  look beautiful on the outside but on the inside are full of dead men’s bones and every kind of impurity. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"In the same way  , on the outside you appear to be   righteous, but on the inside you are full of hypocrisy and wickedness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, you hypocrites!  You build  tombs for the prophets and decorate the monuments of the righteous. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And you say, If we had lived in the days of our  fathers,   we would not have been partners with them in shedding the blood of the prophets. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"So you testify against yourselves that you are the sons of those who murdered the prophets. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Fill up , then, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:32 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Go ahead, then, and complete</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"the measure of the sin of your fathers. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"You snakes! You brood of vipers! How will you escape  the sentence  of hell? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Because of this , I am sending  you prophets and wise men and teachers. Some of them you will kill and crucify, and  others you will flog in your  synagogues and persecute from town to town. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"And so upon you will come all the righteous blood shed on  earth, from the blood of righteous Abel to the blood of Zechariah son of Berechiah, whom you murdered between the temple and the altar. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Truly I tell you, all these things will come upon this  generation. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Lament over Jerusalem"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/13.htm#31|>Luke 13:31–35</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, who kills the prophets and stones those sent to her, how often I have longed to gather your  children together, as  a hen gathers her  chicks under her wings, but  you were unwilling! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Look, your  house is left to you desolate. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:38 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH do not include <i>desolate</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"For I tell you that   you will not see Me again  until  you say, Blessed is He who comes in the name of the Lord.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:39 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 118:26"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"24"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Temple Destruction and Other Signs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/13.htm|>Mark 13:1–8</a>; <a href =|../luke/21.htm#5|>Luke 21:5–9</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"As  Jesus left  the temple and was walking away,  His  disciples came up to Him to point out   its  buildings. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," Do you see all these things?    He replied . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Truly I tell you,  not one stone here will be left on another; every one  will be thrown down. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"While Jesus was sitting on the Mount  of Olives, the disciples came to Him  privately. Tell us, they said, when will these things happen, and what will be the sign of Your  coming and of the end of the age? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"  Jesus answered  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["See to it that no one  deceives you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"For many will come in My  name, claiming, I am the Christ, and will deceive many . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"}," You will hear of wars and rumors of wars, but see to it  that you are not alarmed. These things must happen, but the end is still to come. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"}," Nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom.  There will be famines and earthquakes in various places. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"}," All these are the beginning of birth pains. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Witnessing to All Nations"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/13.htm#9|>Mark 13:9–13</a>; <a href =|../luke/21.htm#10|>Luke 21:10–19</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then they will deliver you over to be persecuted and killed , and you will be hated by all  nations because of My  name. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," At that time many will fall away and will betray  and hate one another, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"and many false prophets will arise and deceive many. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"}," Because of  the multiplication  of wickedness, the love of most will grow cold. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But the one who perseveres to the end  will be saved. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"And this  gospel of the kingdom will be preached in all the world as a testimony to all  nations, and then the end will come. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Abomination of Desolation"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/13.htm#14|>Mark 13:14–23</a>; <a href =|../luke/21.htm#20|>Luke 21:20–24</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"So when you see standing in the holy place the abomination  of desolation,’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Daniel 9:27, Daniel 11:31, and Daniel 12:11."]}],"caller":"+"}," spoken of by the prophet Daniel (let the reader understand), ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"then let those who are in  Judea flee to the mountains. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Let no one on the housetop  come down to retrieve anything from his  house. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"And let no one in the field  return  for his  cloak. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"How miserable  those  days will be for pregnant   and  nursing mothers! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"}," Pray that your  flight  will not occur in the winter or on the Sabbath. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For at that time there will be great tribulation, unseen   from the beginning of the world until  now, and  never to be seen again. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," If  those  days had not been cut short,  nobody   would be saved. But for the sake of the elect, those  days will be cut short. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"At that time, if anyone says to you, Look, here is the Christ! or There He is! do not believe it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"For false Christs and false prophets will appear and perform great signs and wonders to deceive even the elect, if that were possible. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"See, I have told you in advance . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Return of the Son of Man"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/13.htm#24|>Mark 13:24–27</a>; <a href =|../luke/21.htm#25|>Luke 21:25–28</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"So if they tell you, There He is, in the wilderness, do not go out, or, ‘Here He is, in the inner rooms,’ do not believe it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"For just as the lightning comes from the east and flashes as far as the west, so will be the coming of the Son  of Man. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Wherever  there is  a carcass, there the vultures will gather. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"}," Immediately after the tribulation of those  days: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The sun will be darkened, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the moon  will not give its  light; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" the stars will fall from the sky, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the powers of the heavens will be shaken. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>and the celestial bodies will be shaken</i>; see Isaiah 13:10, Isaiah 34:4, and Joel 2:10."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"}," At that time the sign of the Son  of Man will appear in  heaven, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the sky</i>; twice in this verse"]}],"caller":"+"},"and  all the tribes of the earth will mourn.  They will see the Son  of Man coming on the clouds  of heaven with power and great glory. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Daniel 7:13–14."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"And He will send out His  angels with a loud trumpet call, and they will gather His  elect from the four winds, from one end of the heavens to  the other. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Lesson of the Fig Tree"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/13.htm#28|>Mark 13:28–31</a>; <a href =|../luke/21.htm#29|>Luke 21:29–33</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Now learn this lesson ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:32 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>this parable</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"from the fig tree: As soon as  its  branches become tender and sprout  leaves, you know that  summer is near. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"So also, when you see all these things, you will know that He is near, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:33 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>it is near</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"right at the door. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Truly I tell you , this  generation will not  pass away until  all these things have happened. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"}," Heaven and  earth will pass away, but My  words will never  pass away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Readiness at Any Hour"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../genesis/6.htm|>Genesis 6:1–7</a>; <a href =|../mark/13.htm#32|>Mark 13:32–37</a>; <a href =|../luke/12.htm#35|>Luke 12:35–48</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"}," No one knows about that  day or hour, not even the angels  in heaven, nor the Son, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:36 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR do not include <i>nor the Son</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"but  only the Father. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"}," As it was in the days of Noah, so will it be at the coming of the Son  of Man. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"For  in  the days before  the flood, people were eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage, up to the day Noah entered  the ark. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"And  they were oblivious until the flood came and swept them all away .  So will it be at the coming of the Son  of Man. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"}," Two men will be in the field: one will be taken and the other left. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Two women will be grinding at the mill: one will be taken and the other left. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"Therefore keep watch, because  you do not know the day on which your  Lord will come. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"But understand this:  If the homeowner had known in which watch of the night the thief was coming,  he would have kept watch and  would not have let his  house be broken into. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"For this reason , you also must be ready, because the Son  of Man will come at an hour  you do not expect. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"Who then is the faithful and wise servant, whom the master has put in charge of his  household,  to give the others their food at the proper time? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Blessed is that  servant whose   master finds him doing so when he returns. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"Truly I tell you , he will put him in charge  of all his  possessions. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"But suppose that  servant is wicked and says in his  heart, My  master will be away a long time. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"And he begins to beat his  fellow servants and to eat and drink with  drunkards. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"The master of that  servant will come on a day   he does not expect and at an hour   he does not anticipate. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"Then he will cut him to pieces  and assign him  a place with the hypocrites, where there will be  weeping and  gnashing of teeth. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"25"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Ten Virgins"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"At that time the kingdom of heaven will be like ten virgins who took their  lamps and went out to meet the bridegroom. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," Five of them were foolish, and five were wise. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," The foolish ones took their  lamps but did not take along   any extra oil. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"But the wise ones took oil in  flasks along with their  lamps. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"When the bridegroom was delayed,  they all became drowsy and fell asleep. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"}," At midnight  the cry rang out: Here is the bridegroom! Come out to meet him! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then all  the virgins woke up and trimmed their  lamps. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"}," The foolish ones said to the wise, Give us some of your  oil;  our  lamps are going out. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"No,  said the wise ones , or  there may not be enough for both us and you. Instead, go to those who sell oil and buy some for yourselves. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"But while they were on their way to buy it, the bridegroom arrived.  Those who were ready went in with him to the wedding banquet, and the door was shut. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Later  the other virgins arrived and said, Lord, lord, open the door for us! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But  he replied , Truly I tell you,  I do not know you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Therefore keep watch, because  you do not know the day or the hour. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i>when the Son of Man comes</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Parable of the Talents"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/19.htm#11|>Luke 19:11–27</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"For it is just like a man going on a journey, who called his  servants and entrusted them with his  possessions. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"  To one he gave five talents, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent was worth about twenty years’ wages for a laborer."]}],"caller":"+"}," to another two talents, and to another one talent —  each according to his own  ability. And he went on his journey. ",{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<p class=|red|>"]},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The servant who had received the five talents went at once and put them to work ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i><span class=|fnv|>15</span>... And he went on his journey at once. <span class=|fnv|>16</span>... went and put them to work</i>. Translators vary as to the placement of the Greek adverb <i>euthe&#333;s</i> (at once) at the end of verse 15 or at the beginning of verse 16."]}],"caller":"+"},"  and gained five more. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Likewise, the one with the two talents gained two more. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But the servant who had received the one talent went off, dug a hole in the ground, and hid his  master’s  money. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"}," After a long time the master of those  servants returned and settled accounts with them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"}," The servant who had received the five talents came and presented five more . Master, he said, you entrusted me with five talents. See, I have gained five  more. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"His  master replied , Well done, good and faithful servant! You have been faithful with a few things; I will put you in charge of many things. Enter into the joy of your master! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," The servant who had received the two talents also came and said, Master, you entrusted me with two talents. See, I have gained two  more. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"His  master replied , Well done, good and faithful servant! You have been faithful with a few things; I will put you in charge of many things. Enter into the joy of your master! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Finally, the servant who had received the one talent came and said, Master, I knew  that you are a hard man, reaping where  you have not sown and gathering where  you have not scattered seed. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"So I was afraid and went out and hid your  talent in the ground. See, you have what belongs to you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"You wicked,  lazy servant!  replied   his  master. You knew that I reap where  I have not sown and gather where  I have not scattered seed. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Then you should have deposited my  money with the bankers, and  on my return  I would have received  it back with interest. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Therefore take the talent from him and give it to the one who has  ten talents. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"For  everyone who has will be given more, and he will have an abundance. But the one who does not have, even what he has will be taken away from him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And throw that worthless servant into the  outer darkness, where there will be  weeping and  gnashing of teeth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Sheep and the Goats"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"}," When the Son  of Man comes in His  glory, and all the angels with Him,  He will sit on His glorious throne. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"}," All the nations will be gathered before Him, and He will separate the people  one from another, as  a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"  He will place the sheep on His right and the goats on His left. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Then the King will say to those on His right, Come, you who are blessed by My Father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"For I was hungry and you gave Me something to eat, I was thirsty and  you gave Me something to drink, I was a stranger and you took Me in , ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"I was naked and you clothed Me, I was sick and you looked after Me, I was in prison and you visited  Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Then the righteous will answer Him , Lord, when did we see You hungry and feed You, or thirsty and give You something to drink? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"}," When did we see You a stranger and take You in, or naked and clothe You? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"}," When did we see You sick or in prison and visit  You? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"And the King  will reply , Truly I tell you, whatever  you did for one of the least of these  brothers of Mine, you did for Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Then  He will say to those on His left, Depart from Me, you who are cursed, into the  eternal fire  prepared for the devil and his  angels. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"For I was hungry and you gave Me nothing to eat,  I was thirsty and you gave Me nothing to drink  , ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"I was a stranger and  you did not take Me in , I was naked and  you did not clothe Me, I was sick and in prison and  you did not look after Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"And they too will reply , Lord, when did we see You hungry or thirsty or a stranger or naked or sick or in prison, and  did not minister to You? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"Then the King will answer  , Truly I tell you, whatever   you did not do for one of the least of these,  you did not do for Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"And they will go away into eternal punishment, but the righteous into eternal life. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"26"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Plot to Kill Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/14.htm|>Mark 14:1–2</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm|>Luke 22:1–2</a>; <a href =|../john/11.htm#45|>John 11:45–57</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"  When  Jesus had finished saying all these  things, He told  His disciples, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"You know that the Passover is two days away, and the Son  of Man will be handed over  to be crucified. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"At that time the chief priests and  elders of the people assembled in the courtyard of the high priest, whose name was Caiaphas, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"and they conspired to arrest  Jesus covertly and kill Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But not during the feast, they said, or  there may be a riot among the people. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Anointed at Bethany"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/14.htm#3|>Mark 14:3–9</a>; <a href =|../luke/7.htm#36|>Luke 7:36–50</a>; <a href =|../john/12.htm|>John 12:1–8</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"While  Jesus was in Bethany in the home of Simon the Leper, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Aramaic <i>Simon the Potter</i> or <i>Simon the Jar Maker</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"a woman came to Him with an alabaster jar of expensive perfume,  which she poured on His  head as He reclined at the table. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"When the disciples saw this, they were indignant and asked, Why  this  waste? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," This perfume could have been sold at a high price, and the money given to the poor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," Aware of this,  Jesus asked , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Why are you bothering  this woman?  She has done a beautiful deed to Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"}," The poor  you will always have with you, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Deuteronomy 15:11."]}],"caller":"+"},"but you will not always have Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"}," By pouring  this  perfume on Me, she has prepared My  body  for burial. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Truly I tell you, wherever  this  gospel is preached in all the world, what she has done  will also be told in memory of her. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Judas Agrees to Betray Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/14.htm#10|>Mark 14:10–11</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm#3|>Luke 22:3–6</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then one of the Twelve, the one called Judas Iscariot, went to the chief priests ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"and asked, What are you willing to give me if I hand Him over to you? And  they set out for him thirty pieces of silver. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"So from then on Judas looked for an opportunity to betray Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Preparing the Passover"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/14.htm#12|>Mark 14:12–16</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm#7|>Luke 22:7–13</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"}," On the first day of the Feast of Unleavened Bread, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>On the first of the Unleavened</i>; see Exodus 12:14–20."]}],"caller":"+"},"the disciples came  to Jesus and asked, Where do You want us to prepare for You to eat the Passover? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"  He answered, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Go into the city to a certain man and tell him that the Teacher says, My  time is near. I will keep the Passover with My  disciples at your house.’ ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"So the disciples did as  Jesus had directed them and prepared the Passover. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Last Supper"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/14.htm#17|>Mark 14:17–26</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm#14|>Luke 22:14–23</a>; <a href =|../1_corinthians/11.htm#17|>1 Corinthians 11:17–34</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"When evening came, Jesus was reclining with the twelve disciples. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>the Twelve</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"And while they were eating, He said to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Truly I tell you , one of you will betray Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," They were deeply grieved  and began to ask Him one after another, Surely not  I, Lord? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"  Jesus answered , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The one who has dipped his hand into the bowl with Me  will betray Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"}," The Son  of Man will go just as it is written about Him, but woe to that  man by whom He    is betrayed. It would be better for him if he    had not been born. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Then Judas, who would betray Him, said , Surely not I, Rabbi? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jesus answered , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You have said it yourself. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"While they were eating,  Jesus took bread,  spoke a blessing and broke it, and gave it to the disciples, saying, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Take and eat; this is My  body. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Then He took the cup,  gave thanks, and gave it to them, saying, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Drink from it, all of you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"}," This is My  blood of the covenant, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:28 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>the new covenant</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"which is poured out for many for the forgiveness of sins. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"}," I tell you,   I will not drink of this  fruit of the vine from now on until that  day when I drink it anew with you in My  Father’s  kingdom. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And when they had sung a hymn, they went out to the Mount  of Olives. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Predicts Peter’s Denial"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../zechariah/13.htm#7|>Zechariah 13:7–9</a>; <a href =|../mark/14.htm#27|>Mark 14:27–31</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm#31|>Luke 22:31–38</a>; <a href =|../john/13.htm#36|>John 13:36–38</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Then  Jesus said to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" This very night you  will all fall away on account of Me. For it is written: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will strike the Shepherd, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the sheep of the flock will be scattered.’ ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Zechariah 13:7"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"But after  I have risen, I will go ahead of you into  Galilee. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"  Peter  said to Him, Even if all fall away on account of You, I never will. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Truly I tell you,  Jesus declared ,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" this very night, before the rooster crows, you will deny Me three times. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"}," Peter replied , Even if I have to  die with You,   I will never deny You. And all the other disciples said the same thing. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Prays at Gethsemane"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/14.htm#32|>Mark 14:32–42</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm#39|>Luke 22:39–46</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Then  Jesus went with His disciples to a place called Gethsemane, and He told  them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Sit here while  I go over there and pray. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"}," He took with Him  Peter and the two sons of Zebedee and began to be sorrowful and deeply distressed. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Then He said to them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["My  soul is consumed with sorrow to the point of death. Stay here and keep watch with Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"}," Going a little farther, He fell   facedown and prayed  , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["My Father, if it is possible, let this  cup pass from Me. Yet not as I will, but as You will. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"Then Jesus returned to the disciples and found them sleeping. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["  Were you not able to keep watch with Me for one hour?  He asked  Peter. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Watch and pray so that  you will not enter into temptation. For the spirit is willing, but the body is weak. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"  A second time He went away and prayed , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["My Father, if this cup  cannot pass unless  I drink it, may Your  will be done. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"And again Jesus returned and found them sleeping, for their  eyes were heavy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"So He left them and went away once more and prayed  a third time, saying the same thing . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"Then He returned to the disciples and said , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Are you still sleeping   and resting? Look, the hour is near, and the Son  of Man is betrayed into the hands of sinners. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Rise, let us go! See, My  betrayer is approaching! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Betrayal of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/14.htm#43|>Mark 14:43–52</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm#47|>Luke 22:47–53</a>; <a href =|../john/18.htm|>John 18:1–14</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"While Jesus  was still speaking , Judas, one of the Twelve, arrived,  accompanied by  a large crowd armed with swords and clubs, sent from the chief priests and elders of the people. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"Now the betrayer  had arranged a signal with them : The One  I kiss is the man; arrest Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"}," Going directly  to Jesus, he said, Greetings, Rabbi! and kissed Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"Friend,   Jesus replied , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do what you came for.”</span> ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:50 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>“Friend,” Jesus replied, “for what have you come?”</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then the men stepped forward, seized     Jesus, and arrested Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"At this , one of Jesus’ companions    drew his  sword and struck the servant of the high priest, cutting off his  ear. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"Put your  sword back in its  place,  Jesus  said to him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For all who draw the sword will die by the sword. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"  Are you not aware that I can call on My  Father, and He will at once put at My disposal   more than twelve legions of angels? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"But how then would the Scriptures be fulfilled that say it must happen this way? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"At that  time  Jesus said to the crowd, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Have you come out with swords and clubs to arrest Me as you would an outlaw? Every day I sat teaching in the temple courts, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:55 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>the temple</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and  you did not arrest Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"But this has all happened so that the writings of the prophets would be fulfilled. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then all the disciples deserted Him and fled. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus before the Sanhedrin"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/14.htm#53|>Mark 14:53–65</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm#66|>Luke 22:66–71</a>; <a href =|../john/18.htm#19|>John 18:19–24</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57"}," Those who had arrested  Jesus led Him away to the house of Caiaphas the high priest, where the scribes and  elders had gathered. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58"},"But  Peter followed Him at a distance, right up to the courtyard of the high priest. And he went in and sat down with the guards to see the outcome. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59"},"Now the chief priests and the whole Sanhedrin ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:59 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the whole Council</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"were seeking false testimony against  Jesus in order to put Him to death . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60"},"But  they did not find any, though many false witnesses came forward. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Finally  two came forward ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61"},"and declared, This man said, I am able to destroy the temple  of God and rebuild it in three days. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62"},"So the high priest stood up and asked Him, Have You no answer ? What are these men testifying against You? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63"},"But  Jesus remained silent. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then the high priest said to Him, I charge You under oath  by  the living God:  Tell us if You are the Christ, the Son  of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64"},"You have said it yourself,  Jesus answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But I say to all of you, from now on you will see the Son  of Man sitting at the right hand  of Power ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:64 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the right hand of the Mighty One</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and coming on the clouds  of heaven.”</span> ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:64 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Psalm 110:1 and Daniel 7:13."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"65"},"At this, the high priest tore his  clothes and declared, He has blasphemed! Why do we need any more witnesses? Look, now you have heard the blasphemy. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"66"},"What do you think? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" He deserves to die,   they answered . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"67"},"Then they spit in His  face and struck Him.  Others slapped Him ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"68"},"and said, Prophesy to us, Christ! Who   hit You? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Peter Denies Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/14.htm#66|>Mark 14:66–72</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm#54|>Luke 22:54–62</a>; <a href =|../john/18.htm#15|>John 18:15–18</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"69"},"Meanwhile , Peter was sitting out in the courtyard, and a servant girl came up to him. You also were with Jesus the Galilean, she said. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"70"},"But  he denied it before them all :  I do not know what you are talking about. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"71"},"When Peter had gone out to the gateway, another servant girl saw him and said to the people there, This man was with Jesus of Nazareth. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"72"},"And again he denied it with an oath :  I do not know the man! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"73"}," After a little while, those standing nearby came up  to Peter. Surely you  are one of them, they said, for  your  accent gives you away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"74"},"At that he began to curse and swear to them ,  I do not know the man! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And immediately a rooster crowed. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"75"},"Then  Peter remembered the word that Jesus had spoken : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Before the rooster crows, you will deny Me three times. And he went outside and wept bitterly. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"27"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus Delivered to Pilate"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/15.htm|>Mark 15:1–5</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"When morning came, all the chief priests and  elders of the people  conspired against  Jesus to put Him to death . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," They bound Him, led Him away, and handed Him over to Pilate the governor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Judas Hangs Himself"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../zechariah/11.htm#10|>Zechariah 11:10–17</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"When Judas, who had betrayed Him , saw that Jesus was condemned, he was filled with remorse and returned the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and elders. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"I have sinned by betraying innocent blood, he said. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What is that to us?   they replied. You bear the responsibility. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"So Judas threw the silver into the temple and left. Then he went away and hanged himself. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"}," The chief priests picked up the pieces of silver and said,  It is unlawful to put this into the treasury, since it is blood money. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"After conferring together , they used the money to buy the  potter’s field as a burial place for foreigners. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"That is why   it has been called the Field of Blood to  this day. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then what was spoken through Jeremiah the prophet was fulfilled : "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" They took the thirty pieces of silver, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the price set on Him    by the people of Israel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"and they gave them for the  potter’s field, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["as the Lord had commanded me.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Jeremiah 19:1–15, Jeremiah 32:6–9, and Zechariah 11:12–13."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jesus before Pilate"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../luke/23.htm|>Luke 23:1–5</a>; <a href =|../john/18.htm#28|>John 18:28–40</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Meanwhile  Jesus stood before the governor,  who  questioned Him : Are You the King of the Jews? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You have said so,   Jesus replied. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And    when He was accused by the chief priests and elders, He gave no answer . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then  Pilate asked Him,  Do You not hear how many charges they are bringing against You? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"But  Jesus gave no answer , not even to a single charge, much to the governor’s amazement. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Crowd Chooses Barabbas"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/15.htm#6|>Mark 15:6–11</a>; <a href =|../luke/23.htm#13|>Luke 23:13–25</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Now it was the governor’s custom at the feast to release to the crowd a prisoner of their choosing. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"}," At that time they were holding a notorious prisoner named Barabbas. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["SBL and NA <i>Jesus Barabbas</i>; also in verse 17, but universally called <i>Barabbas</i> in verses 20, 21, and 26"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"So  when the crowd had assembled,  Pilate asked them, Which one do you want me to release to you:  Barabbas, or Jesus who is called Christ? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For he knew it was out of envy that they had handed Jesus over to him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"While  Pilate was sitting on the judgment seat, his  wife sent  him this message: Have nothing to do with   that  innocent man, for I have suffered terribly in a dream today because of Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But the chief priests and  elders persuaded the crowds to ask for  Barabbas and to have Jesus put to death  . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Which of the two do you want me to release to you?  asked the governor  . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" Barabbas,   they replied. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"What then should I do with Jesus who is called Christ?  Pilate asked . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" They all answered, Crucify Him! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Why?   asked Pilate. What evil has He done? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But  they shouted all the louder , Crucify Him! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Pilate Washes His Hands"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/15.htm#12|>Mark 15:12–15</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"When  Pilate saw that he was accomplishing nothing, but that instead a riot was breaking out, he took water and washed his hands before the crowd. I am innocent of this man’s blood, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>this blood</i>; BYZ and TR <i>this righteous blood</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"he said. You bear the responsibility.” "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"}," All the people answered , His  blood be on us and on our  children! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"So Pilate released  Barabbas to them. But he had Jesus flogged  , and handed Him over to be crucified. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Soldiers Mock Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/50.htm#4|>Isaiah 50:4–11</a>; <a href =|../mark/15.htm#16|>Mark 15:16–20</a>; <a href =|../luke/22.htm#63|>Luke 22:63–65</a>; <a href =|../john/19.htm|>John 19:1–15</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Then the  governor’s soldiers took  Jesus into the Praetorium and gathered the whole company around Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"}," They stripped Him and put a scarlet robe on Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"And they twisted together a crown of thorns and set it on His  head. They put a staff in His  right hand,  knelt down before Him, and mocked Him, saying, Hail, King of the Jews! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Then they spit on Him and took the staff and struck Him on the head repeatedly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"After  they had mocked Him, they removed  the robe and put His own clothes back on Him. Then they led Him away  to  crucify Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Crucifixion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../psalms/22.htm|>Psalm 22:1–31</a>; <a href =|../mark/15.htm#21|>Mark 15:21–32</a>; <a href =|../luke/23.htm#26|>Luke 23:26–43</a>; <a href =|../john/19.htm#16|>John 19:16–27</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Along the way  they found a man from Cyrene, named Simon, and they forced him to carry the cross of Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"And when they came to a place called Golgotha, which means  The Place of the Skull, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"they offered Him wine to drink, mixed with gall; but after tasting it, He refused  to drink it. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"When they had crucified Him, they divided up His  garments by casting lots. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:35 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Psalm 22:18; TR includes <i>to fulfill what was said through the prophet: “They divided My garments among them, and cast lots for My clothing.”</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"And sitting down, they kept watch over Him there. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Above His  head  they posted the written charge against Him: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["THIS IS JESUS, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["THE KING OF THE JEWS. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"}," Two robbers ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:38 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>insurrectionists</i>; also in verse 44"]}],"caller":"+"},"were crucified with Him, one on His right and the other on His left. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"And those who passed by heaped abuse on Him, shaking their  heads ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"and saying, You who are going to destroy the temple and rebuild it in three days, save Yourself! If You are the Son  of God,  come down from the cross! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"In the same way , the chief priests,   scribes, and elders mocked Him, saying, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"He saved others,  but He cannot save Himself. He is the King of Israel! Let Him come down now from the cross, and we will believe in Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"He trusts in  God. Let God deliver Him now if He wants Him. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:43 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 22:8"]}],"caller":"+"},"For He said,  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I am the Son of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"  In the same way, even the robbers who were crucified with Him berated Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Death of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../psalms/22.htm|>Psalm 22:1–31</a>; <a href =|../mark/15.htm#33|>Mark 15:33–41</a>; <a href =|../luke/23.htm#44|>Luke 23:44–49</a>; <a href =|../john/19.htm#28|>John 19:28–30</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"}," From the sixth hour until the ninth hour ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:45 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, from noon until three in the afternoon"]}],"caller":"+"},"darkness came over all the land. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"}," About the ninth hour  Jesus cried out  in a loud voice , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Eli, Eli, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:46 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH <i>Eloi, Eloi</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"lema sabachthani? which means, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["My God, My God, why  have You forsaken Me?”</span> ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:46 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 22:1"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"When some of those standing there heard this, they said,  He is calling Elijah. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"}," One of them quickly ran and brought a sponge.  He filled it with sour wine, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:48 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>filled it with wine vinegar</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}," put it on a reed, and held it up for Jesus to drink . ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:48 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Psalm 69:21."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"But the others said, Leave Him alone. Let us see if Elijah comes to save Him. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:49 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["WH includes <i>And another took a spear and pierced His side, and water and blood flowed out</i>; see John 19:34."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"When  Jesus had cried out again  in a loud voice, He yielded up His spirit. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"At that moment  the veil of the temple was torn in two from top to bottom.  The earth quaked, and the rocks were split. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"}," The tombs broke open, and the bodies of many  saints who had fallen asleep were raised. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"}," After Jesus’  resurrection, when they had come out of the tombs, they entered  the holy city and appeared to many people. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"When the centurion and those with him who were guarding  Jesus saw the earthquake and all that had happened, they were terrified  and said, Truly this was the Son of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"And many women were there, watching from a distance. They had followed  Jesus from  Galilee to minister to Him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"Among them were Mary  Magdalene,  Mary the mother  of James and Joseph, and the mother of Zebedee’s sons. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Burial of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/53.htm#9|>Isaiah 53:9–12</a>; <a href =|../mark/15.htm#42|>Mark 15:42–47</a>; <a href =|../luke/23.htm#50|>Luke 23:50–56</a>; <a href =|../john/19.htm#38|>John 19:38–42</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57"},"When it was evening, there came a rich man from Arimathea named Joseph, who himself  was a disciple  of Jesus. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58"},"He went  to Pilate to ask for the body  of Jesus, and  Pilate ordered that it be given to him. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59"},"So  Joseph took the body, wrapped it in a clean linen cloth, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60"},"and placed it in his own new  tomb that he had cut into the rock. Then he rolled a great stone across the entrance to the tomb and went away. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61"}," Mary  Magdalene and the other Mary were sitting there opposite the tomb. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Guards at the Tomb"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62"}," The next day, the one  after  Preparation Day, the chief priests and  Pharisees assembled before Pilate. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63"},"Sir, they said, we remember that while He was alive that  deceiver said, ",{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<span class=|red|>"]},"After three days I will rise again. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64"},"So give the order that the tomb be secured until the third day. Otherwise , His  disciples may come and steal Him away  and tell the people He has risen from the dead. And this last deception would be worse than the first. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"65"},"You have a guard,  Pilate said . Go, make the tomb as secure as you know how. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"66"},"So  they went and   secured the tomb by sealing the stone and posting the guard. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"28"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Resurrection"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/16.htm|>Mark 16:1–8</a>; <a href =|../luke/24.htm|>Luke 24:1–12</a>; <a href =|../john/20.htm|>John 20:1–9</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"}," After the Sabbath,  at dawn on the first day of the week, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["28:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>Now after the Sabbaths, it being dawn toward the first of the Sabbaths,</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"Mary  Magdalene and the other Mary went to see the tomb. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," Suddenly there was a great earthquake, for an angel of the Lord descended from heaven,   rolled away the stone, and sat on it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}," His  appearance was like lightning, and his  clothes were white as snow. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"}," The guards trembled in  fear of him and became like dead men. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But the angel  said to the women, Do not be afraid, for I know that you are looking for Jesus, who was crucified. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"He is not here;  He has risen, just as He said! Come, see the place where He lay. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["28:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>where the Lord lay</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then go quickly and tell His  disciples , He has risen from the dead and  is going ahead of you into  Galilee. There you will see Him. See, I have told you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"So they hurried away  from the tomb in fear and great joy, and ran to tell His  disciples. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Suddenly  ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["28:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>They were going to tell His disciples, and suddenly</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"Jesus met them and said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Greetings!   They came to Him, grasped His  feet, and worshiped Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Do not be afraid,  said  Jesus . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Go and tell My  brothers to go to  Galilee. There they will see Me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Report of the Guards"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"While the women were on their way , some of the guards went into the city and reported to the chief priests all that had happened. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And after the chief priests had met with the elders and formed a plan , they gave the soldiers a large sum of money ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"and instructed them: You are to say , His  disciples came by night and stole Him away while we were asleep. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"}," If this report reaches  the governor, we will satisfy him and keep you out of trouble. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"So the guards took the money and did as they were instructed. And this  account has been circulated among the Jews to this very day. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Great Commission"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../mark/16.htm#14|>Mark 16:14–18</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Meanwhile, the eleven disciples went to  Galilee, to the mountain   Jesus had designated . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"When they saw Him, they worshiped Him, but some doubted. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Then  Jesus came to them and said , "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["All authority in heaven and on  earth has been given to Me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Therefore go and make disciples ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["28:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>Having gone, therefore, make disciples</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"of all  nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"and teaching them to obey all that I have commanded you. And surely I am with you always  , even to the end of the age. "]}]}